alled%20these%20scenarios%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGedankenexperiment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGedankenexperiments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20German%20for%20thought%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20name%2C%20Einstein's%20mental%20exercises%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Flost-in-thought-how-important-to-physics-were-einstein-s-imaginings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincorporated%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20actual%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20thought%20experiments%20that%20demonstrate%20some%20of%20Einstein's%20most%20groundbreaking%20discoveries%2C%20including%20his%20special%20and%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einsteins-theory-of-relativity-notes-sold-for-13-million-2021-11%5C%22%3Etheories%20of%20relativity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20would%20happen%20if%20you%20chased%20a%20beam%20of%20light%20as%20it%20moved%20through%20space%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22albert%20einstein%20wears%20a%20suit%20and%20sits%20in%20a%20chair%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652047826e038039826c0b0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat%20happens%20when%20you%20travel%20at%20the%20same%20speed%20as%20a%20beam%20of%20light%3F%3Cp%3ECentral%20Press%2FStringer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEinstein%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pitt.edu%2F~jdnorton%2FGoodies%2FChasing_the_light%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20wondering%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20this%20when%20he%20was%20just%2016%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20could%20somehow%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20light%20and%20travel%20as%20fast%20as%20it%20is%20going%2C%20Einstein%20reasoned%2C%20you%20would%20be%20able%20to%20observe%20the%20light%20frozen%20in%20space.%20But%20since%20he%20knew%20light%20was%20a%20wave%20composed%20of%20changing%20magnetic%20and%20electric%20fields%2C%20it%20couldn't%20truly%20be%20still.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20sees%20in%20this%20paradox%20the%20germ%20of%20the%20special%20relativity%20theory%20is%20already%20contained%2C%26quot%3B%20Einstein%20wrote%20in%20his%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fhardcover%2F9780691183602%2Feinstein-on-einstein%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAutobiographical%20Notes%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20This%20%26quot%3Bspecial%26quot%3B%20theory%20applies%20to%20certain%20relationships%20between%20space%20and%20time%2C%20and%20he%20further%20explored%20it%20with%20another%20thought%20experiment%20involving%20trains%20and%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%202%20people%20experience%20the%20exact%20same%20event%20differently%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-white%20photo%20of%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%20with%20Albert%20Einstein.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c0453bd1a36600194c8019%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221874%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECan%20any%20event%20really%20ever%20be%20simultaneous%3F%3Cp%3ECorbis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you're%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkcts9.pbslearningmedia.org%2Fresource%2Fphy03.sci.phys.energy.sprelativity%2Feinsteins-special-theory-of-relativity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estanding%20on%20a%20train%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20your%20friend%20is%20standing%20outside%20the%20train%2C%20watching%20it%20pass%20by.%20If%20lightning%20struck%20near%20both%20ends%20of%20the%20train%2C%20your%20friend%20would%20see%20both%20bolts%20flash%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20the%20train%2C%20you%20are%20closer%20to%20the%20bolt%20of%20lightning%20you're%20moving%20toward.%20So%20you%20see%20this%20lightning%20first%20because%20the%20light%20has%20a%20shorter%20distance%20to%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20setup%20for%20this%20experiment%20is%20a%20bit%20complicated%20and%20involves%20angled%20mirrors%20and%20poles.%20But%20the%20result%20is%20that%20time%20behaves%20differently%20for%20someone%20moving%20than%20for%20someone%20standing%20still.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20cemented%20Einstein's%20belief%20that%20time%20and%20space%20are%20relative%20and%20simultaneity%20%E2%80%94%20two%20events%20happening%20at%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%94%20depends%20on%20your%20perspective.%20This%20is%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20Einstein's%20special%20theory%20of%20relativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20your%20space-traveling%20twin%20age%20compared%20to%20you%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222337%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Albert%20Einstein%20is%20shown%20seated%20inside%20by%20the%20window%2C%20writing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520489c6e038039826c0df0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221752%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWill%20you%20age%20more%20slowly%20if%20you%20travel%20at%20nearly%20the%20speed%20of%20light%3F%3Cp%3EBettmann%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20you%20have%20a%20twin%20who%20was%20born%20at%20almost%20the%20exact%20same%20time%20as%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20almost%20immediately%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feinstein-reveals-manipulate-time-2016-3%5C%22%3Etwin%20boards%20a%20spaceship%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20launches%20into%20space%20to%20travel%20through%20the%20universe%20at%20nearly%20the%20speed%20of%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%2C%20according%20to%20Einstein's%20special%20theory%20of%20relativity%2C%20time%20moves%20slower%20the%20closer%20you%20reach%20the%20speed%20of%20light%2C%20your%20twin%20in%20the%20spaceship%20would%20age%20more%20slowly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20spaceship%20landed%20back%20on%20Earth%2C%20you%20would%20be%20celebrating%20your%2065th%20birthday%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.omnicalculator.com%2Fphysics%2Ftime-dilation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20twin%3C%2Fa%3E%20hadn't%20even%20turned%2010%20yet%2C%20based%20on%20an%20estimation%20from%20Omni%20Calculator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20your%20elevator%20accelerating%20or%20floating%20in%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22981%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Albert%20Einstein%20sits%20in%20a%20chair%20behind%20a%20wooden%20table%20on%20his%20porch%20at%20home%20in%20Princeton%2C%20New%20Jersey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652048e79f7ca8b2bbdc34c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22735%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhy%20do%20forces%20like%20gravity%20and%20acceleration%20feel%20the%20same%3F%3Cp%3EErnst%20Haas%20%2F%20Contributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20are%20in%20a%20windowless%20elevator%2C%20unable%20to%20see%20what's%20happening%20outside.%20Without%20visual%20cues%2C%20you%20don't%20know%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20stationary%20elevator%20on%20Earth%20or%20in%20space%20being%20hauled%20upwards.%20Gravity's%20tug%20and%20upward%20acceleration%20in%20zero%20gravity%20both%20pull%20you%20to%20the%20floor.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20physics%20of%20both%20events%20is%20the%20same%2C%20Einstein%20decided%2C%20based%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bprinciple%20of%20equivalence.%26quot%3B%20Similarly%2C%20if%20your%20elevator%20were%20to%20plummet%20far%20and%20fast%2C%20you%20would%20float%20as%20though%20you%20were%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20consider%20Einstein's%20previous%20assertion%20that%20time%20and%20space%20are%20relative.%20If%20motion%20can%20affect%20time%20and%20space%20(like%20with%20the%20train%20experiment)%20and%20gravity%20and%20acceleration%20behave%20the%20same%2C%20that%20means%20gravity%20can%20actually%20affect%20time%20and%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20put%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphysics.aps.org%2Farticles%2Fv4%2F43%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebowling%20ball%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20trampoline%2C%20it%20will%20depress%20the%20fabric.%20Place%20marbles%20close%20by%2C%20and%20they%20will%20roll%20toward%20the%20ball.%20Objects%20with%20huge%20mass%20can%20affect%20space-time%20in%20a%20similar%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20of%20gravity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-hole-warps-space-astronomers-see-light-behind-it-2021-8%5C%22%3Ewarp%20space-time%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfa.harvard.edu%2Fresearch%2Fscience-field%2Feinsteins-theory-gravitation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekey%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Einstein's%20general%20theory%20of%20relativity%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F17661-theory-general-relativity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20decade%20after%20the%20special%20theory%20and%20expanded%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20particles%20communicate%20faster%20than%20the%20speed%20of%20light%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Einstein%20sticks%20his%20tongue%20out%20standing%20next%20to%20another%20man%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cc246e0f3dff001956c9da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat%20is%20spooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance%3F%3Cp%3EBettmann%20%2F%20Contributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEinstein%20wasn't%20the%20biggest%20cheerleader%20for%20quantum%20theory.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20argued%20back%20and%20forth%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanhattan-project-scientists-who-won-nobel-prizes-2023-7%5C%22%3Ephysicist%20Niels%20Bohr%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20certain%20occurrences%20that%20he%20believed%20violated%20fundamental%20laws%20of%20physics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Einstein's%20thought%20experiments%20had%20to%20do%20with%20quantum%20entanglement%2C%20which%20he%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquantum-entanglement-einstein-first-picture-2019-7%5C%22%3Espooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20have%20a%20two-sided%20coin%20that%20you%20can%20easily%20split%20in%20half.%20You%20flip%20the%20coin.%20Without%20looking%20at%20the%20outcome%2C%20you%20hand%20one%20side%20to%20your%20friend%20and%20keep%20the%20other%20side%20for%20yourself.%20Then%20your%20friend%20gets%20on%20a%20rocket%20ship%20and%20travels%20across%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20your%20coin%2C%20you%20see%20you're%20holding%20the%20heads%20side%20of%20the%20coin.%20Instantly%20you%20know%20that%20your%20friend%2C%20who%20is%20billions%20of%20light%20years%20away%2C%20has%20the%20tails%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Albert%20Einstein%20taken%20on%20December%2030%2C%201932.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641ca3d9d67fe70018a3776a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22791%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20scientists%20have%20spent%20decades%20researching%20Einstein's%20thought%20experiments.%3Cp%3EBettmann%20%2F%20Contributor%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEinstein's%20version%20of%20this%20thought%20experiment%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20coins%20and%20involves%20entangled%20particles%20that%20share%20a%20wave%20function.%20Both%20particles%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20in%20two%20possible%20states%2C%20spin%20up%20and%20spin%20down.%20Measuring%20one%20gives%20you%20information%20about%20the%20other%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20far%20apart%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20bit%20like%20if%20your%20half%20of%20the%20coin%20was%20neither%20heads%20nor%20tails%20until%20you%20looked%20at%20it.%20Since%20the%20coin%20wasn't%20double-sided%2C%20you%20know%20your%20friend%20has%20tails%20when%20you%20have%20heads.%20But%20Einstein%20thought%20particles%20behaved%20more%20like%20real%20coins.%20They%20had%20some%20inherent%20property%20that%20made%20them%20%26quot%3Bspin%20up%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bspin%20down%26quot%3B%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20scientists%20have%20proven%20him%20wrong%20in%20the%20decades%20since.%20In%202022%2C%20three%20physicists%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Fphysics%2F2022%2Fsummary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20demonstrating%3C%2Fa%3E%20spooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696618571000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520473c6561dd877e735b0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20of%20Einstein's%20most%20defining%20qualities%20was%20his%20remarkable%20ability%20to%20conceptualize%20complex%20scientific%20ideas%20by%20imagining%20real-life%20scenarios.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ali%20Sundermier%2CJenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20May%20See%20Deep%20Recession%2C%20Impacting%20India's%20Markets%2C%20Exports%3A%20Economist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20may%20see%20a%20deep%20recession%20soon%2C%20and%20such%20a%20scenario%20would%20impact%20not%20only%20India's%20services%20sector%2C%20which%20is%20a%20key%20component%20of%20the%20country's%20GDP%2C%20but%20also%20bring%20about%20a%20lot%20of%20volatility%20in%20the%20bond%20and%20equity%20markets%2C%20a%20top%20economist%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exclusive%20conversation%20with%20NDTV%2C%20Neelkanth%20Mishra%2C%20who%20is%20the%20Chief%20Economist%20for%20Axis%20Bank%20and%20the%20part-time%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Unique%20Identification%20Authority%20of%20India%2C%20said%20the%20United%20States%20was%20expected%20to%20enter%20a%20recession%20this%20year%20and%20it%20was%20thought%20its%20GDP%20growth%20would%20fall%2C%20but%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20September%2C%20people%20thought%20that%20there%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%26quot%3B%20and%20there%20would%20not%20be%20a%20recession.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20analysis%20says%20however%20that%2C%20this%20year%2C%20their%20fiscal%20deficit%20has%20gone%20up%20by%204%25%20of%20their%20GDP.%20%C2%A0They%20had%20targeted%20%241%20trillion%20-%20their%20fiscal%20year%20ends%20on%20September%2030%20-%20and%20they%20ended%20up%20with%20a%20figure%20of%20%242%20trillion.%20If%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20is%20so%20high%2C%20there%20can't%20be%20a%20recession.%20The%20problem%20for%20them%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20if%20they%20don't%20keep%20increasing%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%2C%20they%20can't%20sustain%20the%20economy's%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Mishra%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20they%20manage%20to%20keep%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20flat%20next%20year%2C%20which%20is%20a%20problem%20in%20itself%2C%20the%20economy%20will%20go%20into%20a%20recession.%20Because%20of%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20being%20so%20high%2C%20no%20one%20is%20wanting%20to%20buy%20US%20bonds.%20Rates%20are%20rising%20because%20of%20that%2C%20and%20this%20is%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20contraction%20in%20demand%20across%20the%20world.%20So%2C%20the%20recession%20that%20will%20happen%20could%20be%20a%20very%20deep%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20Impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20how%20this%20could%20impact%20India%2C%20Mr%20Mishra%20said%20the%20effects%20could%20be%20felt%20through%20four%20pathways.%20Services%20growth%2C%20which%20is%20already%20slow%2C%20would%20get%20slower.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20US%20sees%20a%20recession.%20Our%20IT%20services%20industry%20and%20our%20business%20services%20exports%20could%20be%20hit.%20Services%20exports%20make%20up%2010%25%20of%20India's%20exports.%20If%20they%20fall%20a%20lot%2C%20we%20could%20lose%201%25%20of%20GDP%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20pathway%20is%20the%20impact%20on%20goods%20exports.%20The%20economist%20said%20goods%20demand%20will%20fall.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20already%20low%20in%20China%2C%20Europe%20and%20Japan%20and%20was%20above%20trend%20in%20the%20US.%20This%20could%20affect%20India's%20goods%20exports%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20risk%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20dumping%20of%20products%20in%20India.%20Mr%20Mishra%20pointed%20out%20that%20If%20India%20remains%20the%20only%20country%20where%20demand%20is%20resilient%2C%20every%20manufacturer%20would%20like%20to%20sell%20here.%20This%20would%20adversely%20affect%20Indian%20manufacturers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20problem%20is%20that%20a%20US%20recession%20would%20affect%20the%20yield%20on%20its%20government%20bond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCost%20of%20capital%20would%20go%20up%20for%20the%20other%20economies.%20Good%20borrowers%20in%20India%2C%20like%20famed%20steel%20companies%2C%20would%20get%20dollar%20loans%20easily%20earlier.%20But%20such%20loans%20have%20not%20been%20available%20for%20the%20past%206-8%20months.%20This%20would%20bring%20about%20a%20lot%20of%20volatility%20in%20financial%20markets%20like%20bond%20markets%20and%20equity%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreparing%20The%20Country%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrice%20of%20crude%20oil%20has%20already%20started%20falling%20in%20the%20past%20two-three%20days%20because%20people%20have%20started%20fearing%20a%20recession.%20If%20the%20US%20goes%20into%20a%20recession%20in%20May-June%20next%20year%2C%20oil%20prices%20will%20come%20down.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20oil%20prices%20rise%2C%20it%20will%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20steps%20India%20can%20take%20to%20tackle%20all%20of%20this%2C%20Mr%20Mishra%20said%20the%20focus%20should%20be%20on%20macroeconomic%20stability%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20risk-taking%2C%20to%20be%20able%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20waves%20of%20turbulence.%20%26quot%3BMacroeconomic%20stability%20gives%20you%20growth%20for%20a%20longer%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EState%20Vs%20Centre%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20report%20stating%20that%20if%20India%20gets%20a%20stable%20government%20after%202024%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20will%20rise%20by%2010%25%20and%20could%20fall%20by%2020-60%25%20if%20that%20does%20not%20happen%2C%20the%20economist%20said%20this%20is%20a%20very%20wrong%20way%20of%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20impact%20of%20the%20central%20government%20on%20the%20economy%20comes%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%20It%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20a%20big%20way%2C%20but%20in%203-5%20years.%20State%20governments%20have%20a%20bigger%20role%20to%20play%20in%20the%20near-term%20economic%20momentum%20-%20whether%20investments%20are%20being%20done%20by%20foreign%20and%20private%20companies%20-%20and%20this%20will%20not%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Mishra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20fertility%20rate%20is%20falling%20in%20India%20and%20the%20net%20savings%20are%20increasing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20being%20seen%20in%20the%20increased%20investment%20in%20equity%20markets%20-%2030-35%20billion%20dollars%20are%20being%20invested%20each%20year.%20A%20change%20in%20government%20will%20not%20affect%20this.%20Housing%20construction%20is%20behind%20this%20current%20strength%20in%20India's%20economy%2C%20and%20this%20will%20not%20change%20either.%20Nobody%20will%20stop%20building%20their%20house%20if%20the%20government%20changes.%20According%20to%20me%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20sensationalist%20forecast%20is%20totally%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20The%20Middle%20Class%20Should%20Do%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20whether%20he%20has%20any%20advice%20for%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20Mr%20Mishra%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20next%20year%20or%20year-and-a-half%20will%20be%20very%20turbulent%20for%20the%20global%20economy.%20If%20we%20are%20lucky%2C%20that%20is.%20If%20not%2C%20it%20could%20extend%20to%20five%20years.%20I%20would%20advise%20precaution.%20Looking%20at%20the%20Indian%20economy%20in%20the%20next%205-7%20years%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20too%20much%20of%20a%20cause%20for%20worry.%20Its%20trajectory%20looks%20good%20for%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696618440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F51dl8qio_economist-neelkanth-mishra-650_625x300_07_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fus-may-see-deep-recession-could-impact-indias