pan%20from%201914%20until%20its%20capture%20by%20the%20United%20States%20during%20World%20War%20II.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%201948%20and%201958%2C%20the%20US%20conducted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bikiniatoll.info%2Fhistory-of-enewetak%2F%5C%22%3E43%20nuclear%20tests%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Enewetak%20Atoll%2C%20including%20the%20first%20test%20of%20the%20hydrogen%20bomb.%20Because%20of%20the%20nuclear%20testing%2C%20the%20lagoon%20surrounding%20the%20chain%20of%20islands%20became%20irradiated%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20sand%20and%20soil%20on%20the%20islands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201972%2C%20the%20US%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fpsad-79-54%5C%22%3E%24100%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20area.%20Clean-up%20crews%20mixed%2080%2C000%20cubic%20meters%20of%20contaminated%20soil%20and%20debris%20with%20cement%20that%20they%20poured%20into%20a%20blast%20crater%20that%20was%2030%20feet%20deep%20and%20360%20feet%20wide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20the%20clean-up%20team%20constructed%20a%20dome%20made%20of%20358%20concrete%20panels%20to%20cover%20the%20radioactive%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESea%20turtles%20in%20the%20area%20by%20Enewetak%20Atoll%20have%20been%20found%20to%20have%20traces%20of%20radiation%20in%20their%20shells.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20sea%20turtle%20swimming%20underwater.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adb0d4ff1e30019476b16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20sea%20turtle%20swimming%20among%20dead%20corals%20of%20a%20reef.%3Cp%3EMLADEN%20ANTONOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20cleanup%20at%20Enewetak%20Atoll%2C%20turtles%20were%20found%20with%20radiation%20in%20the%20layers%20of%20their%20shells.%20The%20leading%20theory%20is%20that%20the%20clean-up%20efforts%20disrupted%20radioactive%20sediment%20in%20the%20lagoon%20near%20Enewetak%20Atoll%20and%20the%20turtles%20swallowed%20the%20sediment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EChernobyl%20was%20a%20nuclear%20meltdown%20event%20in%201986%2C%20and%20its%20impacts%20are%20still%20being%20felt%20today.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Chernobyl%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ad7f603971f001932091e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20external%20view%20of%20Chernobyl%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant.%3Cp%3EAnatoli%20Kliashchuk%2FSygma%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2026%2C%201986%2C%20one%20of%20the%20reactors%20at%20the%20Chernobyl%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20went%20out%20of%20control%20during%20a%20test%20at%20low%20power.%20The%20result%20was%20an%20explosion%20and%20a%20fire%20that%20released%20over%20100%20radioactive%20elements%20into%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20uranium%20fuel%20melted%20through%20protective%20barriers%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20protective%20concrete%20dome%20led%20to%20the%20release%20of%20radioactive%20elements%20like%20plutonium%2C%20iodine%2C%20strontium%2C%20and%20cesium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20explosion%20killed%20two%20workers%2C%20and%20three%20months%20after%20the%20event%2C%2028%20firemen%20and%20emergency%20workers%20died%20from%20radiation%20sickness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWild%20boars%20in%20Bavaria%2C%20Germany%2C%20are%20still%20being%20found%20with%20radioactive%20elements%20in%20their%20bodies.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20wild%20boar%20with%20an%20apple%20in%20its%20mouth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adc1303971f0019320abc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20wild%20boar%20holds%20an%20apple%20in%20its%20mouth.%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Armer%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoars%20forage%20for%20mushrooms%20and%20truffles%20which%20feed%20off%20nutrients%20in%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20nuclear%20tests%20are%20done%2C%20nuclear%20elements%20swell%20into%20the%20sky%2C%20get%20carried%20by%20the%20wind%2C%20and%20settle%20onto%20the%20ground.%20As%20mushrooms%20grow%2C%20they%20absorb%20radiation%20from%20that%20nuclear%20fallout%20from%20the%20ground.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWild%20boars%20in%20Bavaria%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da6d4fc3b0255d86d374124fc4fc1772cce08d90a971244b68483880c674d0af7%26postID%3D651b167bb970ec721e9a854a%26postSlug%3Dradioactive-animal-species-nuclear-disasters-testing-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%252Fanimals%252Farticle%252Fradioactive-animals-nuclear-testing-disasters%253Frid%253D1CF29FDA20D05EDBA0FEB1B16047B848%2526cmpid%253Dorg%25253Dngp%253A%253Amc%25253Dcrm-email%253A%253Asrc%25253Dngp%253A%253Acmp%25253Deditorial%253A%253Aadd%25253DDaily_NL_History_Thursday_20230921%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%2015%2C000%20becquerels%20of%20radiation%20for%20every%20kilogram%20of%20meat.%20The%20European%20safety%20limit%20is%20600%20becquerels%20per%20kilogram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20packs%20of%20wild%20dogs%20surrounding%20Chernobyl%20have%20also%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20meltdown.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pack%20of%20wild%20dogs%20roams%20an%20outdoor%20market%20in%20Russia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adfab03971f0019320c13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20pack%20of%20wild%20dogs%20roams%20an%20outdoor%20market%20in%20Russia.%3Cp%3EMENAHEM%20KAHANA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20700%20dogs%20living%20near%20Chernobyl%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20descendants%20of%20the%20dogs%20left%20behind%20by%20people%20who%20evacuated%20the%20area%20after%20the%20meltdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20been%20studying%20mutations%20in%20the%20dog's%20genomes%20and%20DNA%20as%20well%20as%20measuring%20the%20radiation%20in%20their%20bones.%20The%20dogs%20in%20Chernobyl%20live%20much%20shorter%20lives%20than%20the%20average%20dog%20with%20a%20lifespan%20of%20three%20to%20four%20years%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20average%2010%20to%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EReindeer%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Norway%20have%20also%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20meltdown%20at%20Chernobyl.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20herd%20of%20reindeer%20running%20in%20a%20group%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adcf44ff1e30019476bc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20large%20group%20of%20reindeer%20running%20together%20in%20a%20herd.%3Cp%3EOLIVIER%20MORIN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENuclear%20sediment%20from%20Chernobyl%20was%20carried%20by%20the%20wind%20up%20to%20Norway%20where%20it%20fell%20into%20the%20soil%20in%20rain%20droplets.%20The%20radiated%20elements%20were%20absorbed%20from%20the%20soil%20by%20moss%20and%20fungus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReindeer%20in%20the%20area%20would%20feed%20on%20the%20moss%20and%20fungus.%20Immediately%20after%20the%20fallout%2C%20they%20could%20be%20found%20with%20levels%20of%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20becquerels%20per%20kilogram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20radiation%20levels%20in%20reindeer%20are%20now%20below%20safety%20standards%2C%20but%20every%20now%20and%20then%20spikes%20are%20seen%20in%20reindeer%20meat%20that%20exceed%202%2C000%20becquerels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%202011%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20disaster%20resulted%20in%20the%20evacuation%20of%20thousands%20and%20is%20the%20second-worst%20nuclear%20disaster%20in%20history.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222249%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20in%20construction%20hats%20walk%20on%20a%20concrete%20pier%20with%20the%20Fukushima%20power%20plant%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adab74ff1e30019476ad0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20men%20in%20construction%20hats%20walk%20on%20a%20concrete%20pier%20with%20the%20Fukushima%20power%20plant%20in%20the%20background.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20a%209.0%20earthquake%20triggered%20a%2050-foot%20tsunami%20that%20disabled%20the%20cooling%20and%20power%20supply%20of%20three%20reactors%20at%20the%20Fukushima%20nuclear%20plant.%20The%20result%20was%20the%20meltdown%20of%20the%20three%20reactors%20within%20three%20days%20of%20the%20incident.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20100%2C000%20people%20were%20evacuated%20from%20their%20homes%20following%20the%20disaster%2C%20and%20many%20people%20have%20yet%20to%20return%20to%20their%20homes%20due%20to%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Japanese%20macaques%2C%20also%20known%20as%20snow%20monkeys%2C%20were%20found%20to%20have%20increased%20levels%20of%20radiation%20after%20the%20Fukushima%20disaster.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20four%20Japanese%20Macaques%20in%20a%20hot%20spring%20in%20the%20snow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ade924ff1e30019476c4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMacaque%20monkeys%20bathe%20in%20a%20hot%20spring.%3Cp%3ETomohiro%20Ohsumi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20Fukushima%20disaster%2C%20macaques%20were%20found%20with%20levels%20of%20concentrated%20cesium%20up%20to%2013%2C500%20becquerels%20per%20kilogram.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20their%20diet%20of%20mushrooms%2C%20tree%20bark%2C%20and%20bamboo%20%E2%80%94%20all%20food%20sources%20that%20absorb%20radioactive%20cesium%20from%20the%20ground%20%E2%80%94%20the%20macaques%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20found%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0068530%5C%22%3Eradioactive%20elements%20in%20them%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20believe%20that%20the%20long-term%20effects%20of%20radiation%20in%20the%20macaque%20population%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjeffmcmahon%2F2017%2F10%2F30%2Fthree-ways-radiation-has-changed-the-monkeys-of-fukushima-a-warning-for-humans%2F%3Fsh%3D7ace068765ea%5C%22%3Esmaller%20heads%2C%20smaller%20brains%2C%20delayed%20growth%2C%20and%20anemia%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-animal-species-nuclear-disasters-testing-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696616579000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b16f7617692f0d03cdcd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-animal-species-nuclear-disasters-testing-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nuclear%20fallout%20can%20have%20a%20lasting%20impact%20on%20surrounding%20communities%20and%20environments.%20Some%20animal%20species%20near%20nuclear%20sites%20are%20still%20found%20to%20be%20radioactive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elias%20Chavez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-animal-species-nucle