ision%20meant%20that%20Pakistan%20would%20continue%20to%20wallow%20in%20confusion%2C%20unable%20to%20fix%20its%20national%20priorities%20and%20goals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2040-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%2C%20who%20is%20also%20one%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20leading%20nuclear%20physicists%2C%20said%20Jinnah%20never%20made%20clear%20whether%20he%20wanted%20Pakistan%20to%20be%20a%20Muslim%20or%20Islamic%20state%20or%20whether%20it%20should%20be%20a%20secular%20state.%20He%20said%20things%20to%20support%20both%20interpretations%20at%20different%20stages%20of%20his%20life.%20Consequently%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20he%20created%20remains%20mired%20in%20confusion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FMS5LfDw3JT4%3Fsi%3Dm0Z-zqyCykg2YV28%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20Jinnah%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfixated%20on%20one%20goal%2C%20to%20create%20a%20country%20for%20the%20Muslims%20of%20India.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20he%20had%20no%20thought%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf.%20Hoodbhoy%20quotes%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20response%20at%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20in%201945%20and%201946%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20what%20sort%20of%20country%20Pakistan%20would%20be.%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20he%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnyone%20who%20asks%20me%20what%20Pakistan%20will%20be%20is%20an%20enemy%20of%20Pakistan.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%2C%20was%20a%20brilliant%20tactical%20answer%20because%20anything%20more%20specific%20would%20have%20angered%20and%20annoyed%20the%20many%20constituencies%20that%20Jinnah%20needed%20to%20please%20and%20keep%20on%20side.%20However%2C%20it%20also%20meant%2C%20that%20there%20was%20no%20planning%20and%20thinking%20about%20the%20sort%20of%20country%20that%20emerged%20after%20independence%20on%20August%2014%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20after%20independence%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Cangularities%20and%20bumps%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20Jinnah%20called%20them%2C%20would%20iron%20themselves%20out.%20On%20other%20occasions%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20said%20Jinnah%20was%20inclined%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshrug%20such%20issues%20off%E2%80%9D.%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20this%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20profound%20mistake%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20asked%20if%20Jinnah%20were%20to%20miraculously%20materialise%20today%20what%20would%20he%20make%20of%20Pakistan%20in%202023%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20%E2%80%9Che%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20particularly%20happy%20that%20his%20liberal%20and%20pluralistic%20impulses%20have%20been%20subjugated%2C%20he%20would%20be%20very%20unhappy%20to%20see%20the%20exodus%20of%20Hindus%2C%20the%20break-up%20of%20the%20country%20and%20the%20Baloch%20still%20struggling%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20Jinnah%20the%20person%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20said%20Jinnah%20had%20%E2%80%9Cno%20profound%20understanding%20of%20Islam%2C%20he%20never%20quoted%20a%20verse%20from%20the%20Quran%2C%20he%20never%20referred%20to%20the%20Hadith%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20known%20instance%20of%20Jinnah%20having%20criticised%20Hinduism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf.%20Hoodbhoy%20says%20before%201937%20Jinnah%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20free%20of%20religious%20prejudice%20and%20not%20particularly%20attached%20to%20Islam%E2%80%9D.%20After%201937%2C%20when%20the%20Muslim%20League%20was%20badly%20defeated%20even%20in%20the%20Muslim-majority%20provinces%20that%20became%20Pakistan%2C%20Jinnah%20used%20religion%20to%20create%20a%20constituency%20for%20himself%20and%20a%20demand%20for%20Pakistan.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Jinnah%20used%20religion%20strategically%20as%20a%20political%20tool%20and%20did%20not%20see%20it%20as%20a%20personal%20or%20ideological%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20man%20and%20his%20personal%20knowledge%20of%20Islam%2C%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnable%20to%20read%20any%20Islamic%20language%20%E2%80%93%20Arabic%2C%20Persian%20or%20Urdu%20%E2%80%A6%20culturally%2C%20Jinnah%20was%20more%20British%20than%20Indian.%20Those%20of%20strong%20religious%20faith%20despised%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20man%20and%20his%20style%20Prof.%20Hoodbhoy%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWith%20Victorian%20manners%2C%20this%20impeccably%20dressed%20secular%20and%20anglicised%20man%20had%20a%20connoisseur%E2%80%99s%20appreciation%20of%20fine%20foods%20and%20wines.%20His%20culinary%20choices%20%E2%80%93%20which%20included%20ham%20and%20pork%20%E2%80%93%20outraged%20the%20strict%20Muslim.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20wish%20to%20understand%20Muhammad%20Ali%20Jinnah%20better%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20the%20different%20sides%20of%20his%20personality%20and%20character%2C%20the%20contradictions%20in%20his%20political%20strategy%2C%20the%20lapses%20and%20even%20failures%20in%20the%20way%20Pakistan%20has%20developed%20and%20how%20much%20of%20that%20is%20attributable%20to%20Jinnah%2C%20this%20is%20an%20interview%20you%20should%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696601573000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06192336%2F222222.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-jinnah-wasnt-a-visionary-or-deep-thinker-which-is-why-pakistan-has-wallowed-in-confusion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pervez%20Hoodbhoy%2C%20who%20came%20out%20with%20his%20new%20book%20'Pakistan%3A%20Origins%2C%20Identity%20and%20Future'%2C%20talks%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20in%20an%20analytical%20interview%20about%20the%20founder%20of%2