-12978246%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnasa-to-explore-giant-metal-asteroid-psyche-heres-why-it-could-reveal-secrets-about-solar-system-12978246%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnasa-to-explore-giant-metal-asteroid-psyche-heres-why-it-could-reveal-secrets-about-solar-system-12978246%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Activists%20Lambast%20Odisha%20Government's%20Controversial%20Land%20Acquisition%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBhubaneswar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20passage%20of%20a%20controversial%20land%20acquisition%20Bill%20in%20late%20September%20by%20the%20Odisha%20assembly%20amidst%20a%20boycott%20by%20the%20opposition%20has%20evoked%20sharp%20reactions%20from%20major%20political%20parties%20and%20rights%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Fair%20Compensation%20and%20Transparency%20in%20Land%20Acquisition%2C%20Rehabilitation%20and%20Resettlement%20(Odisha%20Amendment)%20Bill%20(RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR)%2C%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fodisha-assembly-passes-bill-exempting-projects-from-social-impact-assessment%2Farticle67353558.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Odisha%2520Legislative%2520Assembly%2520on%2Cimpact%2520assessment%2520(SIA)%2520and%2520special%5C%22%3Epassed%20on%20September%2027%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20exempt%20%E2%80%98strategic%20and%20development%20projects%E2%80%99%20from%20social%20impact%20assessment%20(SIA)%20and%20special%20provisions%20to%20ensure%20food%20security%20%E2%80%93%20which%20were%20hitherto%20considered%20mandatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20brute%20majority%20(114%20out%20of%20147%20seats)%20that%20the%20ruling%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20enjoys%20in%20the%20legislature%2C%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed%20without%20a%20hitch.%20But%20the%20opposition%20parties%20staged%20a%20walkout%20to%20register%20their%20protest.%20Making%20a%20statement%2C%20revenue%20and%20disaster%20management%20minister%20Sudam%20Marndi%20said%20that%20mandatory%20provisions%20in%20the%20RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR%20Bill%20like%20SIA%20and%20special%20provisions%20for%20food%20security%20were%20delaying%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land.%20The%20minister%20referred%20to%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20Make-In-Odisha%20conclaves%20aimed%20at%20attracting%20private%20investments%20in%20mega%20projects%20across%20sectors.%20Fast-tracking%20these%20projects%20depends%20a%20lot%20on%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20provide%20trouble-free%20land%20to%20the%20project%20proponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bill%20will%20enable%20the%20state%20government%20to%20issue%20notifications%20exempting%20projects%20vital%20to%20national%20security%20or%20defence%20and%20infrastructure%20development%20from%20SIA%20and%20food%20security%20provisions.%20Projects%20like%20affordable%20housing%2C%20industrial%20corridors%20set%20up%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20including%20highways%20and%20railways%2C%20and%20industrial%20projects%20involving%20displacement%20of%20100%20families%20or%20less%20or%20acquisition%20of%20private%20land%20of%20500%20acres%20or%20less%20will%20be%20exempted%20from%20conducting%20mandatory%20SIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR%20Act%2C%202013%2C%20a%20central%20law%20which%20makes%20SIA%20mandatory%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccauses%20a%20delay%20in%20acquisition%20of%20land.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERights%20activist%20and%20leader%20of%20Lok%20Shakti%20Abhiyan%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkidnapping-of-anti-mining-activist-samantara-casts-spotlight-on-bauxite-mining-protests-in-odisha%5C%22%3EPrafulla%20Samantara%3C%2Fa%3E%20lambasted%20the%20state%20government%20for%20bringing%20amending%20the%20Central%20law%20to%20facilitate%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land%20for%20various%20projects.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20new%20Bill%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Central%20law.%20It%20is%20anti-democratic%20and%20anti-people.%20It%20is%20now%20more%20than%20obvious%20that%20the%20government%20is%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20corporates%20without%20bothering%20about%20the%20plight%20of%20common%20people%2C%20especially%20the%20tiller%20of%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Samatara%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20engaged%20in%20a%20fight%20for%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20land%20that%20a%20corporate%20house%20is%20trying%20to%20mine%20for%20bauxite%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fodishatv.in%2Fnews%2Fodisha%2Fresentment-erupts-over-vedanta-s-bauxite-mining-at-sijimali-in-odisha-214162%5C%22%3ESijimali%20area%20of%20Rayagada%20district%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20that%20for%20land%20acquisition%2C%20not%20only%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20tiller%20of%20the%20land%20should%20be%20taken%20but%20also%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20gram%20sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22890%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298.png%20890w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298-300x116.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671968%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22343%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrafulla%20Samantara.%20Photo%3A%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ELawyer-cum-activist%20Siddhartha%20Nayak%2C%20who%20was%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20lights%20of%20the%20movement%20against%20mining%20in%20the%20Niyamgiri%20hills%2C%20was%20also%20critical%20of%20the%20government.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20most%20undemocratic%20step%20taken%20by%20the%20government%20for%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land.%20Its%20prime%20victims%20will%20be%20poor%20tribals%20who%20are%20fighting%20for%20their%20land%20rights%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20state.%20We%20need%20to%20launch%20a%20state-wide%20movement%20to%20oppose%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%20He%20said%20the%20Bill%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20desperation%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20government%2C%20which%20has%20failed%20to%20acquire%20land%20peacefully%20for%20certain%20mega%20projects%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20ArcelorMittal%20pulled%20out%20of%20Odisha%20after%20scrapping%20its%20%2412%20billion%20(Rs%2050%2C000%20crore)%20steel%20plant%20project%20because%20of%20problems%20in%20acquiring%20land.%20This%20was%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20showcase%20investments%20in%20major%20projects%20as%20an%20achievement%20on%20the%20industrialisation%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20state%20government%20suffered%20another%20major%20blow%20when%20POSCO%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth-largest%20steelmaker%2C%20withdrew%20from%20its%2012-million-tonne-capacity%20steel%20project%20in%20Jagatsinghpur%20district.%20This%20was%20at%20that%20time%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20(FDI)%20in%20the%20steel%20sector%20in%20the%20country.%20However%2C%20the%20South%20Korean%20company%20had%20to%20retract%20because%20land%20acquisition%20for%20the%20project%20led%20to%20widespread%20violence%20at%20the%20project%20site.%20POSCO%E2%80%99s%20withdrawal%20also%20affected%20the%20ruling%20BJD%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fodisha-deja-vu-dhinkia-protest-jindal-steel-project-posco%5C%22%3EOdisha%3A%20D%C3%A9j%C3%A0%20Vu%20in%20Dhinkia%20as%20People%20Renew%20Protests%20Against%20Jindal%E2%80%99s%20Steel%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20such%20cases%20which%20create%20problems%20for%20the%20state%20government.%20The%20government%20wants%20to%20avoid%20such%20hurdles%20at%20any%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELingraj%20Azad%2C%20another%20tall%20leader%20of%20the%20Niyamgiri%20movement%2C%20described%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20latest%20move%20as%20disgraceful.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20like%20looting%20someone%E2%80%99s%20land%20without%20even%20seeking%20their%20opinion.%20There%20is%20no%20respect%20for%20public%20opinion%20now.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20development%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20people%20because%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20development%20is%20to%20better%20the%20lives%20of%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Azad.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELawyer-cum-activist%20Siddhartha%20Nayak%20felt%20that%20by%20passing%20such%20laws%2C%20the%20government%20was%20actually%20inviting%20trouble%20for%20itself%20as%20there%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20resistance.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20seen%20this%20in%20Niyamgiri%2C%20where%20they%20had%20once%20backed%20attempts%20at%20bauxite%20mining%20by%20a%20major%20corporate%20house%20which%20is%20now%20eyeing%20bauxite%20reserves%20in%20Sijimali.%20The%20government%20and%20the%20corporate%20house%20thought%20that%20the%20tribal%20people%20resisting%20mining%20in%20the%20Niyamgiri%20hills%20would%20back%20out.%20They%20also%20tried%20to%20divide%20them%20using%20various%20means.%20But%20ultimately%20the%20people%20won%20and%20Niyamgiri%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20fight%20for%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20over%20their%20land%20and%20the%20natural%20resources%20bestowed%20upon%20them%20by%20God.%20This%20Bill%20will%20similarly%20provoke%20common%20people%20to%20fight%20attempts%20by%20big%20corporate%20houses%20to%20take%20away%20their%20land%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20Congress%20leader%20and%20former%20MLA%20Lalatendu%20Mohapatra%20described%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20despite%20a%20boycott%20by%20the%20opposition%20parties%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunfortunate%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20sign%20of%20growing%20intolerance%20on%20the%20part%20of%20powers%20that%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20state%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20Bhrigu%20Buxipatra%20said%20that%20the%20government%20may%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20heavy%20price%20for%20going%20against%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20and%20forcing%20its%20brand%20of%20development%20on%20them.%20%E2%80%9CDevelopment%20has%20to%20be%20harmonious%20and%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20wishes%20of%20the%20people.%20If%20it%20does%20not%20respect%20their%20wishes%20it%20is%20bound%20to%20spawn%20strife%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Buxipatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20BJD%20leader%20Narayan%20Pradhan%20asserted%20that%20the%20government%20had%20taken%20the%20right%20step%20keeping%20because%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cpave%20the%20way%20for%20rapid%20industrialisation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fashutoshmishra%5C%22%3EAshutosh%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20Odisha-based%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696593645000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Factivists-lambast-odisha-governments-controversial-land-acquisition-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bill%2C%20passed%20on%20September%2027%2C%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20exempt%20%E2%80%98strategic%20and%20development%20projects%E2%80%99%20from%20social%20impact%20assessment%20and%20special%20provisions%20to%20ensure%20food%20security.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Factivists-lambast-odisha-governments-controversial-land-acquisition-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Experts%20Have%20Been%20Predicting%20The%20Death%20Of%20Cable%20TV%20For%20Years.%20Is%20The%20End%20Now%20In%20Sight%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22As%20more%20U.S.%20households%20turn%20to%20streaming%20and%20distributors%20have%20less%20incentive%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20business%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20in%20for%20a%20shake-up.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696592757000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.huffingtonpost.com%2Fasset%2F651f27df2200001a00f37e0c.gif%3Fcache%3Dgjal8vg17a%26ops%3D224_126%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fcable-tv-business-future_n_651d6ec4e4b00623d35ecd5a%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20more%20U.S.%20households%20turn%20to%20streaming%20and%20distributors%20have%20less%20incentive%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20business%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20in%20for%20a%20shake-up.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fcable-tv-business-future_n_651d6ec4e4b00623d35ecd5a%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-huffpost-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fcable-tv-business-future_n_651d6ec4e4b00623d35ecd5a%2Famp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fcable-tv-business-future_n_651d6ec4e4b00623d35ecd5a%2Famp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Is%20Willing%20to%20Find%20a%20Long-Term%20Solution%20to%20the%20Cauvery%20Dispute%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F16201207%2Ffile-Cauvery.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20verdict%20issued%20by%20the%20Cauvery%20tribunal%20has%20created%20friction%20between%20the%20government%20and%20farmers%20in%20South%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20week%20of%20September%202023%2C%20Karnataka%20observed%20two%20public%20bandhs%20called%20within%20a%20gap%20of%20two%20days.%20There%20was%20a%20split%20between%20the%20politically%20backed%20protesters%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20unions.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20bandhs%2C%20protests%2C%20demonstrations%2C%20instances%20of%20violence%2C%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20aggression%20in%20the%20last%20four%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20Bengalurian%20who%20grew%20up%20with%20frequent%20holidays%20due%20to%20the%20Cauvery%20issue%2C%20I%20can%20attest%20that%20there%20is%20more%20politics%20at%20play%20in%20the%20Cauvery%20matter%20than%20just%20the%20water-sharing%20formula.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20one%20wants%20to%20invest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20silt%20has%20decreased%20the%20water%20storage%20capacity%20of%20the%20Cauvery%20dam.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20a%20government%20initiative%20financially%20support%20brick%20factories%20using%20silt%20from%20the%20Cauvery%20dam%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20asked%20my%20writer%20friend%2C%20albeit%20in%20a%20lighter%20tone.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%201932%2C%20the%20silt%20has%20been%20removed%20yearly%20during%20summer%2C%20and%20the%20dam%20remains%20crystal%20clear%2C%E2%80%9D%20my%20friend%20responded%20sarcastically.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20dam%2C%20Kannambadi%20Katte%2C%20which%20was%20later%20called%20KRS%20dam%2C%20was%20designed%20for%20a%20specific%20purpose.%20Today%2C%20without%20the%20Cauvery%20water%20from%20the%20KRS%20dam%2C%20ten%20districts%20in%20southern%20Karnataka%2C%20including%20Mysore%20and%20Bengaluru%20urban%20districts%2C%20which%20entirely%20depend%20on%20rainwater%2C%20are%20facing%20arid%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBuilt%20in%20the%201900s%2C%20no%20one%20anticipated%20water%20demand%20a%20century%20later.%20Moreover%2C%20irrigation%20is%20necessary%20for%20southern%20Karnataka%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20farmers%20due%20to%20changes%20in%20crop%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKarnataka%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Kerala%2C%20and%20Puducherry%20want%20more%20water%20for%20their%20urban%20needs%20and%20agriculture%2C%20but%20no%20one%20is%20ready%20to%20take%20even%20a%20small%20step%20to%20improve%20the%20dam%E2%80%99s%20storage%20facility.%20If%20there%20was%20a%20yearly%20silt%20removal%20mechanism%20in%20place%2C%20we%20could%20increase%20our%20storage%20capacity%20by%20at%20least%202.5%20thousand%20million%20cubic%20feet%20more%2C%20as%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstarofmysore.com%2Fsilt-eats-into-storage-capacity-of-krs-kabini-harangi-dams%2F%5C%22%3Eby%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstarofmysore.com%2Ftag%2Fbapu-lingaraj-urs%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBapu%20Lingaraj%20Urs%2C%202023%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20All%20three%20states%20and%20the%20Union%20territory%20want%20their%20share%20of%20water%2C%20however%2C%20no%20one%20appears%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20find%20a%20long-term%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUrban%20expansion%20heavily%20relies%20on%20exploiting%20water%20resources.%20For%20instance%2C%20Bengaluru%E2%80%99s%20water%20demand%20has%20changed%20exponentially.%20In%201995%2C%20there%20were%2087%20wards%20(councils).%20Now%20there%20are%20more%20than%20200%20wards%2C%20including%20the%20newly%20formed%20ones.%20The%20IT%20boom%20in%20Bengaluru%20has%20changed%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20water%20map.%20This%20has%20increased%20the%20need%20for%20more%20Cauvery%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%2C%20sand%20mining%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20is%20happening%20at%20an%20unprecedented%20pace%2C%20depleting%20the%20essential%20water%20bed%20of%20the%20Cauvery%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20Kuruvai%20crop%20(short-duration%20paddy%20grown%20in%20the%20mid-monsoon%20period)%20heavily%20depends%20on%20the%20Cauvery%20river.%20Both%20urbanisation%20and%20ecological%20destruction%20have%20affected%20the%20demand-supply%20chain%20of%20Cauvery%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20root%20issue%20is%20crucial%3B%20otherwise%2C%20actions%20taken%20may%20simply%20serve%20to%20gain%20political%20leverage%20without%20effectively%20resolving%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Cauvery%20tribunal%20was%20constituted%20in%201990.%20However%2C%20since%20then%2C%20instead%20of%20finding%20solutions%2C%20the%20focus%20largely%20remained%20on%20politicising%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20direction%20issued%20by%20the%20Cauvery%20tribunal%20led%20to%20court%20revisions%20and%20ended%20with%20violent%20protests%20and%20attacks%20by%20the%20Kannadigas%20and%20Tamilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20unions%20continued%20to%20show%20their%20dissatisfaction%20through%20protests.%20Pro-Kannada%20organisations%20were%20divided%20into%20hundreds%20of%20factions%2C%20often%20taking%20to%20the%20streets%20to%20prove%20their%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20instead%20of%20addressing%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20genuine%20concerns%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20political%20leadership%20has%20attempted%20to%20capitalise%20on%20this%20issue%20for%20political%20gains.%20With%20the%202023%20state%20elections%20already%20lost%20and%20the%202024%20general%20election%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20the%20state%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20might%20see%20Cauvery%20as%20an%20influential%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20alliance%20between%20Congress%20and%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20puts%20the%20Karnataka%20state%20Congress%20leadership%20in%20a%20difficult%20position%20to%20address%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2Ffile-20170614-15456-1nv2bsf.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-148352%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22566%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESand%20mining%20on%20the%20Cauvery%20river%20in%202017.%20Prashanth%20NS%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20is%20the%20rain%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20northern%20Karnataka%20received%20average%20rainfall%2C%20but%20the%20southern%20Karnataka%20districts%20faced%20a%20significant%20deficiency%20in%20rainfall%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Cauvery%20catchment%20area.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20underground%20borewells%20and%20lakes%20dried%20up%20by%20early%20August%20in%20the%20rain-dependent%20areas.%20It%20appears%20that%20we%20aren%E2%80%99t%20prepared%20for%20a%20year%20with%20a%20rainfall%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20ignored%20every%20opportunity%20to%20harvest%20rainwater%2C%20including%20mandating%20every%20household%20in%20the%20metro%20city%20to%20include%20a%20rainwater%20system.%20In%20September%2C%20Karnataka%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcabinet-sub-committee-recommends-195-taluks-to-be-declared-droughthit-101694630691989.html%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%20191%20taluks%20as%20drought-hit%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20Karnataka%20highlight%20the%20Kuruvai%20crop%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20while%20Tamil%20Nadu%20farmers%20draw%20attention%20to%20the%20sugarcane%20crop%20grown%20in%20southern%20Karnataka%2C%20which%20is%20water-intensive.%20Both%20paddy%20and%20sugarcane%20are%20considered%20%E2%80%98masculine%20crops%E2%80%99%20due%20to%20the%20effort%20and%20scale%20needed%20to%20grow%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20Cauvery%20river%20is%20not%20sufficient%20for%20both%20states%20at%20this%20point.%20These%20issues%20cannot%20be%20resolved%20by%20legal%20or%20political%20interventions%20alone%2C%20unless%20farmers%20on%20both%20sides%20contemplate%20their%20cultivating%20methods%20and%20the%20profitability%20of%20these%20water-intensive%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20groups%20have%20not%20been%20included%20in%20any%20decisions%20regarding%20the%20Cauvery.%20Their%20opinions%20might%20have%20been%20recorded%2C%20but%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20include%20them%20in%20the%20decision-making%20process.%20Their%20economy%20is%20directly%20connected%20to%20the%20amount%20of%20water%20reaching%20their%20land.%20There%20is%20no%20contention%20during%20excess%20rainfall%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20arises%20when%20it%20is%20deficient.%20There%20should%20be%20some%20standard%20procurement%20during%20distress%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20we%20have%20to%20depend%20on%20large%20dams%2C%20which%20always%20raise%20environmental%20concerns%2C%20and%20give%20rise%20to%20contention%20between%20states%3F%20If%20minor%20irrigation%20projects%20and%20traditional%20water%20harvesting%20methods%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eper%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalrepository.unm.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Freferer%3D%26httpsredir%3D1%26article%3D1189%26context%3Dnrj%5C%22%3EGovindaswamy%2C%202008%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20encouraged%20along%20the%20805%20kilometre%20Cauvery%20basin%2C%20this%20could%20have%20allowed%20underground%20water%20to%20recharge.%20The%20practical%20utilisation%20of%20gram%20panchayats%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20change%20the%20efforts%20at%20the%20grassroot%20levels%20in%20improving%20the%20conservation%20of%20rain%20and%20river%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIrrespective%20of%20the%20size%20of%20dams%2C%20there%20are%20serious%20ecological%20concerns%20that%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fcauvery-manage-demand-not-supply-25326%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Y.K.%20Alagh%20committee%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20water%20disrupting%20could%20only%20be%20solved%20by%20the%20farmers%20mutually.%20It%20is%20impossible%20to%20solve%20this%20matter%20through%20any%20other%20means.%20The%20crop%20pattern%20should%20change%20from%20upper%20reaches%20to%20tail-end%20fields%2C%20and%20a%20crop%20should%20be%20decided%20based%20on%20water%20availability.%20Otherwise%2C%20ritualistic%20aggression%20won%E2%80%99t%20provide%20any%20solution%2C%20except%20disrupting%20the%20daily%20lives%20of%20the%20weaker%20sections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELost%20identity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20is%20the%20rain%20in%20your%20place%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20asked%20my%20farmer%20friend%2C%20who%20was%20practising%20natural%20farming%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Bengaluru.%20After%20a%20long%20sigh%2C%20he%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20rain%20has%20lost%20its%20identity.%20No%20thunder%2C%20lightning%2C%20or%20rhythm.%20It%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20thunderous%20rain%20(referring%20to%20the%20Uttare%20rain%20of%20mid-September%20in%20Karnataka).%20This%20rain%20is%20sufficient%20to%20grow%20short%20Ragi%20(finger%20millet)%20but%20nothing%20else.%20Water%20is%20not%20flowing%20further%3B%20it%20is%20simply%20absorbed%20by%20the%20soil.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20changing%20weather%20patterns%2C%20no%20one%20knows%20when%20it%20will%20rain.%20We%20have%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20harvest%20when%20it%20falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.%20Shantharaju%20is%20a%20media%20teacher%20at%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20documentary%20filmmaker%20and%20a%20freelance%20writer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696591842000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F16201207%2Ffile-Cauvery.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fwho-is-willing-to-find-a-long-term-solution-to-the-cauvery-dispute%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20Bengalurian%20who%20grew%20up%20with%20frequent%20holidays%20due%20to%20the%20Cauvery%20issue%2C%20I%20can%20attest%20that%20there%20is%20more%20politics%20at%20play%20in%20the%20Cauvery%20matter%20than%20just%20the%20water-sharing%20f