re%20held%20on%20October%203%20after%20daylong%20questioning%20by%20Delhi%20Police.%20On%20the%20same%20day%2C%20several%20journalists%20and%20commentators%20with%20links%20to%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20raided%2C%20questioned%20and%20had%20their%20devices%20seized%2C%20in%20what%20is%20being%20called%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20attacks%20on%20independent%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakravorty%20have%20both%20moved%20court%20challenging%20the%20first%20information%20report%20%E2%80%93%20invoking%20charges%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20%E2%80%93%20registered%20by%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20Special%20Cell%2C%20their%20arrests%20and%20the%20order%20on%20a%20seven-day%20police%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20matters%20were%20urgently%20listed%20before%20Justice%20Tushar%20Rao%20Gedela.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20day%20ago%2C%20a%20Delhi%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdelhi-police-opposes-newsclick-editors-plea-for-copy-of-the-fir-under-which-he-is-arrested%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Purkayastha%E2%80%99s%20plea%20to%20be%20provided%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20FIR%20under%20which%20he%20has%20been%20arrested.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20had%20opposed%20the%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-terror-fir-against-newsclick-names-chinese-firms-xiaomi-vivo-puts-lawyers-in-crosshairs%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20on%20the%20FIR%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20surrounding%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98larger%20criminal%20conspiracy%E2%80%99%20involving%20the%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20infusion%20of%20funds%E2%80%9D%20by%20Chinese%20companies%20Xiaomi%20and%20Vivo%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cspirited%20defence%20of%20legal%20cases%E2%80%9D%20against%20these%20telecom%20firms%20by%20%E2%80%9CGautam%20Bhatia%E2%80%9D%20who%20is%20described%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98key%20person%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20respondent%2C%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20said%20there%20are%20certain%20facts%20which%20were%20stated%20which%20he%20does%20not%20know.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20to%20take%20instructions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%20said%20this%20is%20illegal%20and%20that%20the%20arrested%20are%20entitled%20to%20be%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sibal%20pressed%20for%20interim%20release%2C%20the%20Justice%20Gedela%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20issue%20is%2C%20the%20allegations%20don%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20be%20of%20such%20nature%20which%20will%20get%20you%20released%20immediately.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20something%20is%20amiss%20in%20the%20remand%20order.%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Mehta%2C%20tell%20us%E2%80%A6The%20remand%20order%2C%20there%20appears%20to%20be%20something%20which%20is%20missing%20there%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%206%20AM%20and%20the%20counsel%20was%20not%20heard%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20the%20remand%20application%20does%20not%20disclose%20the%20ground%20of%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CApparently%20in%20the%20remand%20application%2C%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20disclose%20the%20ground%20of%20arrest.%20Today%20there%20is%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20which%20is%20staring%20in%20the%20eye%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20asked%20for%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20petitions%20and%20posted%20the%20matter%20for%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20case%20diaries%20will%20be%20presented%20in%20court%20on%20Monday%2C%20SG%20Mehta%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnnecessary%20hype%20is%20created.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20directed%20the%20investigating%20officer%20to%20ensure%20Amit%20Chakravorty%E2%80%99s%20health%20is%20not%20compromised%20with%20in%20any%20way.%20Chakravorty%20is%20disabled.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696589000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F14115727%2FPrabir-Newsclick.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnewsclick-prabir-purkayastha-amit-chakravorty-delhi-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20remand%20application%20does%20not%20%26quot%3Bdisclose%20the%20ground%20of%20arrest.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnewsclick-prabir-purkayastha-amit-chakravorty-delhi-high-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%20Presents%20a%20Dilemma%20for%20Narendra%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20was%201998.%20It%20was%20the%2012th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20and%20the%20first%20NDA%20government%20led%20by%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20would%20be%20in%20office%20for%2013%20months%20until%201999.%20Nitish%20Kumar%20having%20only%20recently%20broken%20away%20from%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20led%20by%20his%20erstwhile%20best%20friend%20Lalu%20Yadav%2C%20floated%20the%20Samata%20Party%20with%20George%20Fernandes%2C%20Syed%20Shahabuddin%2C%20Abdul%20Ghafoor%20and%20a%20few%20others.%20An%20OBC%20showboy%2C%20he%20was%20a%20big%20catch%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20was%20rewarded%20by%20Vajpayee%20with%20the%20coveted%20Railways%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENitish%20took%20his%20newfound%20status%20a%20little%20too%20seriously%2C%20more%20so%20perhaps%20because%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eb%C3%AAte%20noire%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Ram%20Vilas%20Paswan%20had%20preceded%20him%20as%20Railway%20minister%20in%20the%20United%20Front%20governments%20led%20by%20HD%20Deve%20Gowda%20and%20IK%20Gujral.%20At%20the%20instance%20of%20Mandal%20messiah%20VP%20Singh%2C%20the%20UF%20government%20(1996-98)%20had%20selected%20and%20got%20elected%20KR%20Narayanan%2C%20a%20Dalit%20career%20diplomat%2C%20as%20the%20eighth%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERam%20Vilas%20Paswan%2C%20the%20sole%20Janata%20Dal-United%20(JD-U)%20MP%20in%20the%2012th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20had%20floated%20the%20SC%2FDalit%20MPs%E2%80%99%20Forum%20and%20held%20its%20meetings%20in%20Room%20Number%2062%20or%2054%20on%20the%20first%20floor%20of%20Parliament%20House%20in%20the%2011th%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Attempting%20to%20outdo%20Paswan%2C%20Nitish%20floated%20the%20OBC%20MPs%E2%80%99%20forum%20and%20even%20invited%20Kalyan%20Singh%2C%20then%20UP%20chief%20minister%2C%20to%20attend.%20Kalyan%2C%20a%20vocal%20votary%20of%20backward%20empowerment%2C%20agreed.%20Kalyan%20led%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20OBC%20MPs%20from%20UP.%20The%20BJP%20was%20and%20remains%20the%20party%20with%20the%20most%20OBC%20MPs.%20Add%20to%20that%20OBC%20MPs%20from%20allies%20like%20the%20Samata%20Party%2C%20the%20AIADMK%20and%20others%2C%20and%20the%20OBCs%20constituted%20a%20very%20large%20part%20of%20the%20ruling%20NDA.%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20move%20set%20alarm%20bells%20ringing%20in%20BJP%20circles%2C%20also%20partly%20because%20Vajpayee%20seemed%20to%20hold%20the%20OBCs%20in%20some%20disdain.%20Incidentally%2C%20in%20the%2013th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20which%20lasted%20almost%20a%20full%20term%2C%20both%20Paswan%20and%20Sharad%20Yadav%2C%20the%20brain%20behind%20Mandal%2C%20joined%20the%20NDA%20government%20and%20became%20ministers.%20Thereafter%2C%20the%20SC%20MPs%E2%80%99%20Forum%20was%20not%20heard%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22BJP%E2%80%99s%20NDA%20Allies%20Sing%20a%20Different%20Tune%2C%20Reiterate%20Demand%20for%20Caste%20Census%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-nda-allies-caste-census%5C%22%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20NDA%20Allies%20Sing%20a%20Different%20Tune%2C%20Reiterate%20Demand%20for%20Caste%20Census%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20pitch%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EMandir%20wahin%20banayenge%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20demand%20to%20demolish%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%20and%20construct%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ebhavya%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(magnificent)%20Ram%20temple%20at%20the%20same%20spot%2C%20resonated%20well%20with%20a%20large%20section%20of%20the%20Hindu%20population%20in%20the%20cow%20belt%2C%20and%20contributed%20to%20undermining%20VP%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20political%20ace%2C%20the%20empowerment%20of%20OBCs%20through%20acceptance%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%20report%20in%201990.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20seesaw%20battle%20between%20Mandal%20and%20Kamandal%20has%20gone%20on%2C%20sometimes%20covertly%20but%20very%20often%20overtly%2C%20led%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav.%20The%20BJP%2C%20on%20its%20part%2C%20has%20been%20playing%20a%20duplicitous%20game.%20While%20it%20wants%20to%20%E2%80%95%20and%20has%20mostly%20succeeded%20%E2%80%95%20in%20attracting%20prominent%20OBC%20vote%20banks%20by%20showcasing%20first%20Kalyan%20and%20now%20Modi%2C%20it%20is%20determined%20not%20to%20allow%20the%20ghost%20of%20Mandal%20ghost%20to%20rise%20again%20to%20haunt%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20news%20of%20Nitish%E2%80%99%20invitation%20to%20Kalyan%20Singh%20reached%20the%20BJP%20top%20brass%2C%20it%20sent%20tremors%20through%20the%20party.%20Satyadeo%20Singh%2C%20a%20diehard%20RSS%20man%2C%20BJP%20MP%20and%20close%20confidant%20of%20Vajpayee%2C%20told%20some%20of%20us%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20that%20any%20BJP%20MP%20or%20leader%2C%20even%20Kalyan%20Singh%2C%20who%20stepped%20into%20the%20room%20allotted%20for%20this%20meeting%2C%20would%20not%20come%20out%20of%20it%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20Why%20the%20BJP%20Is%20Jittery%20and%20INDIA%20Bloc%20Upbeat%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-census-bjp-india-bloc%5C%22%3EBihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20Why%20the%20BJP%20Is%20Jittery%20and%20INDIA%20Bloc%20Upbeat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20that%20clear%20warning%2C%20the%20meeting%20never%20took%20place%20and%20we%20never%20again%20heard%20of%20the%20OBC%20MPs%E2%80%99%20forum.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20recall%20this%20as%20the%20BJP%20plays%20a%20double%20game%20yet%20again.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20is%20still%20trying%20hard%20to%20scuttle%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20which%20showed%2C%20as%20most%20of%20us%20expected%2C%20that%20the%20backwards%20constitute%20the%20largest%20chunk%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20over%2063%25.%20If%20the%20caste%20census%20is%20held%20nationally%2C%20as%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Opposition%20INDIA%20bloc%20is%20demanding%2C%20its%20result%20may%20not%20be%20very%20different%20from%20the%20Bihar%20survey.%20Now%2C%20the%20BJP%20cannot%20bank%20only%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20OBC%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20Modi%20said%20in%20Raipur%20the%20other%20day%20that%20the%20caste%20survey%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20divide%20Hindu%20society%2C%20but%20he%20also%20pretended%20to%20be%20concerned%20about%20Muslims%2C%20and%20said%20that%20it%20would%20go%20against%20Muslims%2C%20forgetting%20that%20the%20implementation%20of%20Mandal%20already%20provides%20for%20about%208%25%20quota%20for%20OBC%20Muslims%20within%20the%2027.5%25%20OBC%20reservations.%20Moreover%2C%20Modi%20himself%20is%20trying%20to%20attract%20Pasmanda%20Muslims%20by%20offering%20them%20EBC%20status.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Bihar%20BJP%20is%20trying%20its%20best%20to%20push%20the%20caste%20survey%20back%20in%20the%20box%2C%20asserting%20that%20Muslims%20already%20enjoy%20quota%20as%20EBCs.%20The%20long%20and%20short%20of%20it%20is%20that%20Modi%20and%20his%20party%20are%20now%20at%20a%20loss%2C%20and%20do%20not%20know%20how%20to%20address%20the%20caste%20issues%20that%20the%20survey%20has%20foregrounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFaraz%20Ahmad%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696588216000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-survey-presents-a-dilemma-for-narendra-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20caste%20census%20is%20held%20nationally%2C%20as%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Opposition%20INDIA%20bloc%20is%20demanding%2C%20its%20result%20may%20not%20be%20very%20different%20from%20the%20Bihar%20survey.%20Now%2C%20the%20BJP%20cannot%20bank%20only%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20OBC%20claims.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-survey-presents-a-dilemma-for-narendra-modi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disney%20in%20talks%20with%20Gautam%20Adani%2C%20Sun%20TV%20to%20sell%20its%20India%20assets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696588084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F15%2Ffull%2F1694747772-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdisney-in-talks-with-gautam-adani-sun-tv-to-sell-its-india-assets-123100600738_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Disney%20is%20likely%20getting%20a%20boost%20as%20marquee%20global%20brands%20line%20up%20to%20tap%20India's%20massive%20consumer%20base%2C%20with%20advertising%20slots%20being%20sold%20at%20%243%2C600%20a%20second%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdisney-in-talks-with-gautam-adani-sun-tv-to-sell-its-india-assets-123100600738_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdisney-in-talks-with-gautam-adani-sun-tv-to-sell-its-india-assets-123100600738_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdisney-in-talks-with-gautam-adani-sun-tv-to-sell-its-india-assets-123100600738_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Censorship%20Regime%20Creating%20Uneven%20Playing%20Field%20Ahead%20of%202024%20Election%3A%20Freedom%20House%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F30141618%2FScreenshot-2022-06-30-at-2.16.06-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20expanding%20censorship%20regime%20is%20creating%20an%20uneven%20playing%20field%20by%20silencing%20criticism%20of%20and%20independent%20reporting%20on%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20a%20new%20report%20by%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFreedom%20House%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20a%20Washington%20DC-based%20non-profit%2C%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreedomhouse.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FFreedom-on-the-net-2023-DigitalBooklet.pdf%5C%22%3Etitled%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%98Freedom%20on%20the%20Net%202023%3A%20The%20Repressive%20Power%20of%20Artificial%20Intelligence%E2%80%99%2C%20has%20raised%20concerns%20over%20the%20increasing%20use%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20by%20governments%20for%20censorship%20and%20spread%20of%20disinformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20covers%20developments%20between%20June%202022%20and%20May%202023.%20It%20evaluates%20internet%20freedom%20in%2070%20countries%2C%20accounting%20for%2088%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20Internet%20users.%20This%20is%20the%2013th%20edition%20of%20its%20annual%20study%20of%20human%20rights%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20Hindu%20nationalist%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20have%20incorporated%20censorship%2C%20including%20the%20use%20of%20automated%20systems%2C%20into%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20legal%20framework.%20The%20Information%20Technology%20(Intermediary%20Guidelines%20and%20Digital%20Media%20Ethics%20Code)%20Rules%20require%20large%20social%20media%20platforms%20to%20use%20AI-based%20moderation%20tools%20for%20broadly%20defined%20types%20of%20content%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20such%20as%20speech%20that%20could%20undermine%20public%20order%2C%20decency%2C%20morality%2C%20or%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%2C%20and%20security%2C%20or%20content%20that%20officials%20had%20previously%20ordered%20removed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20cites%20the%20ban%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20documentary%20about%20communal%20violence%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20as%20chief%20minister%20in%20Gujarat.%20In%20February%20this%20year%2C%20the%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20ministry%20used%20its%20emergency%20powers%20under%20Rule%2016(3)%20of%20the%20IT%20Rules%2C%202021%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fpm-narendra-modi-bbc-documentary-centre-blocks-tweets-youtube-videos-8396076%2F%5C%22%3Edirected%3C%2Fa%3E%20YouTube%20and%20Twitter%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-govt-directs-youtube-twitter-to-take-down-links-containing-bbcs-gujarat-2002-documentary%5C%22%3Etake%20down%20tweets%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20linked%20to%20the%20controversial%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20documentary%20%E2%80%98India%3A%20The%20Modi%20Question%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBecause%20the%20government%20ordered%20the%20restriction%20of%20the%20documentary%2C%20the%20IT%20Rules%20require%20the%20two%20platforms%20to%20use%20automated%20scanning%20tools%20to%20sweep%20up%20any%20additional%20posts%20that%20share%20the%20film.%20As%20the%20country%20prepares%20for%20general%20elections%20in%202024%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20expanding%20censorship%20regime%20is%20creating%20an%20uneven%20playing%20field%20by%20silencing%20criticism%20of%20and%20independent%20reporting%20on%20the%20ruling%20party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20in%20more%20authoritarian%20contexts%2C%20automated%20censorship%20systems%20could%20close%20what%20little%20space%20remains%20for%20online%20expression.%20It%20further%20said%20that%20automated%20content%20moderation%20systems%20have%20a%20positive%20role%20in%20handling%20large-scale%20content%20moderation%20tasks%2C%20such%20as%20reviewing%20harmful%20content%20like%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20imagery%20and%20graphic%20violence%2C%20which%20can%20be%20distressing%20for%20human%20moderators.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20when%20these%20systems%20are%20used%20appropriately%2C%20they%20can%20excessively%20or%20inconsistently%20flag%20online%20material%2C%20especially%20in%20languages%20other%20than%20English%20or%20slang%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20political%2C%20social%2C%20and%20religious%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20mitigate%20this%20risk%20and%20ensure%20that%20these%20systems%20uphold%20information%20integrity%2C%20it%20is%20important%20for%20online%20content%20and%20AI%20regulations%20to%20be%20based%20on%20human%20rights%20principles.%20This%20should%20involve%20requirements%20for%20audits%2C%20increased%20transparency%20regarding%20algorithm%20use%20and%20impact%2C%20as%20well%20as%20mechanisms%20for%20notice%2C%20explanation%2C%20redress%2C%20and%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Freedom%20House%20report%20evaluates%20countries%20on%20five%20censorship%20methods%20%E2%80%93%20Internet%20connectivity%20restrictions%2C%20blocks%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20blocks%20on%20websites%2C%20blocks%20on%20VPNs%2C%20and%20forced%20removal%20of%20content.%20India%20engaged%20in%20all%20of%20them%20except%20one%20(VPN%20blocking)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fglobal-net-freedom-on-the-decline-indias-censorship-regime-creating-uneven-playing-field-freedom-house-report%2Farticle67384799.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20figured%20among%20the%20list%20of%20countries%20that%20%E2%80%9Cblocked%20websites%20hosting%20political%2C%20social%2C%20or%20religious%20content%E2%80%9D%2C%20deliberately%20disrupted%20ICT%20networks%2C%20used%20pro-government%20commentators%20to%20manipulate%20online%20discussions%2C%20and%20conducted%20%E2%80%9Ctechnical%20attacks%20against%20government%20critics%20or%20human%20rights%20organisations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20range%20of%201%20to%20100%20where%20%E2%80%98100%E2%80%99%20represented%20highest%20digital%20freedom%20and%20%E2%80%981%E2%80%99%20the%20worst%20repression%2C%20India%20scored%2050%2C%20while%20Iceland%2C%20with%2094%2C%20emerged%20as%20the%20country%20with%20the%20best%20climate%20of%20Internet%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696586411000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F30141618%2FScreenshot-2022-06-30-at-2.16.06-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmodi-govts-censorship-regime-creating-uneven-playing-field-ahead-of-2024-election-freedom-house%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20Hindu%20nationalist%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20have%20incorporated%20censorship%2C%20including%20the%20use%20of%20automated%20systems%2C%20into%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20legal%20framework%2C'%20noted%20the%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmodi-govts-censorship-regime-creating-uneven-playing-field-ahead-of-2024-election-freedom-house%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20Expanded%2C%20its%20Relationship%20With%20Britannia%20Kept%20Changing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06131950%2F1.-Foster-8.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%201648%20to%201861%2C%20the%20East%20India%20Company%E2%80%99s%20headquarters%20were%20on%20Leadenhall%20Street%2C%20just%20down%20the%20road%20from%20the%20Bank%20of%20England%2C%20in%20the%20City%20of%20London.%20East%20India%20House%20was%20rebuilt%20twice%2C%20with%20new%20areas%20being%20constructed%20on%20both%20occasions%20for%20the%20display%20of%20artworks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20these%20paintings%20and%20sculptures%20showed%20the%20men%20who%20served%20the%20Company%20as%20soldiers%2C%20ambassadors%2C%20administrators%2C%20and%20kings.%20The%20only%20female%20representations%20inside%20East%20India%20House%20were%20personifications%20of%20territories%20or%20virtues.%20Britannia%2C%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20British%20state%2C%20appeared%20most%20frequently%2C%20and%20was%20often%20accompanied%20by%20a%20woman%20representing%20India%20or%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20sculptures%20of%20Britannia%20were%20specially%20commissioned%20by%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20as%20part%20of%20East%20India%20House%E2%80%99s%20reconstructions%20in%201730%20and%20the%20late%201790s.%20The%20first%20of%20these%2C%20a%20marble%20relief%20titled%20%E2%80%9CBritannia%20presented%20with%20riches%20from%20the%20East%E2%80%9D%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20known%20representations%20of%20Britannia%20in%20British%20art.%20The%20other%20was%20part%20of%20East%20India%20House%E2%80%99s%20monumental%20entrance%20portico.%20Both%20sculptures%20show%20Britannia%20surrounded%20by%20women%20who%20represent%20either%20territories%20or%20virtues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20white%20marble%20relief%20of%20Britannia%2C%20made%20by%20John%20Michael%20Rysbrack%2C%20was%20placed%20inside%20East%20India%20House%20in%201730%20as%20part%20of%20the%20building%E2%80%99s%20reconstruction%20by%20Theodor%20Jacobsen.%20It%20shows%20her%20seated%20on%20the%20left%2C%20being%20approached%20by%20three%20women%20who%20represent%20India%2C%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20India%20is%20shown%20at%20the%20front%2C%20proffering%20a%20casket%20of%20treasure%20to%20Britannia.%20In%20the%20sculpture%E2%80%99s%20lower%20right%20side%2C%20Father%20Thames%20is%20shown%20lounging%20in%20front%20of%20an%20athletic%20man%20who%20is%20busy%20securing%20a%20crate%20of%20goods.%20The%20sculpture%20was%20installed%20above%20the%20fireplace%2C%20inside%20East%20India%20House%E2%80%99s%20perfectly%20cubical%20Directors%E2%80%99%20Court%20Room.%20This%20was%20where%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20decisions%20were%20made%20by%2014%20of%20its%20highest-ranking%20shareholders.%20In%201730%2C%20when%20the%20sculpture%20was%20installed%2C%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20prime%20objective%20was%20to%20earn%20profit%20through%20trade.%20Fifteen%20years%20later%2C%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20founded%20a%20private%20army%20in%20South%20Asia%20and%20began%20its%20transformation%20into%20an%20imperial%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20sculpture%20of%20Britannia%2C%20completed%20in%201798%2C%20was%20by%20John%20Bacon%20and%20was%20part%20of%20East%20India%20House%E2%80%99s%20second%20reconstruction%20by%20Richard%20Jupp%20in%20the%201790s.%20It%20was%20positioned%20on%20the%20outside%20of%20the%20building%2C%20on%20the%20portico%20above%20its%20main%20entrance%20on%20Leadenhall%20Street.%20The%20figures%20surrounding%20Britannia%20are%20completely%20different%20from%20those%20in%20the%20previous%20sculpture.%20Asia%20kneels%20before%20Britannia%2C%20presenting%20her%20with%20treasure.%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20are%20gone%20and%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20female%20figures%20representing%20concepts%20and%20virtues%20such%20as%20Navigation%2C%20Integrity%2C%20Justice%20and%20Liberty.%20King%20George%20III%2C%20dressed%20in%20Roman%20military%20uniform%2C%20stands%20beside%20Britannia%2C%20holding%20the%20%E2%80%9Cshield%20of%20protection%E2%80%9D%20over%20her%20head.%20At%20the%20far-left%20corner%20of%20the%20composition%2C%20The%20Ganges%20reclines%20supinely%20in%20a%20sari%2C%20while%20Father%20Thames%20takes%20his%20place%20at%20the%20far-right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132109%2F2.-P2203.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132109%2F2.-P2203.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132109%2F2.-P2203-300x182.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132109%2F2.-P2203-1024x620.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678591%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22726%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJohn%20Bacon%E2%80%99s%20sculpted%20pediment%20on%20the%20fa%C3%A7ade%20of%20East%20India%20House%2C%20unveiled%20in%201798.%20It%20was%20destroyed%20when%20East%20India%20House%20was%20demolished%20in%201862.(British%20Library%2C%20P2203)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20449px)%2085vw%2C%20449px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132229%2F3.-detail-of-P2203.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22449%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132229%2F3.-detail-of-P2203.jpg%20449w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132229%2F3.-detail-of-P2203-300x293.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678594%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDetail%20of%20above%20showing%20Britannia%20with%20Asia%20at%20her%20feet%20and%20King%20George%20III%20at%20her%20side.%20(British%20Library%2C%20P2203)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20busy%20sculptural%20programme%20on%20the%20new%20entrance%20portico%20publicly%20expressed%20how%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20wanted%20to%20be%20publicly%20perceived.%20Anyone%20who%20walked%20down%20London%E2%80%99s%20Leadenhall%20Street%20in%201798%20would%20have%20recognised%20Britannia%20seated%20at%20its%20centre.%20This%20is%20because%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20in%201797%2C%20the%20new%20cartwheel%20penny%20had%20been%20minted.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20coin%20showing%20Britannia%20to%20be%20mass%20produced%20with%20steam-driven%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20373px)%2085vw%2C%20373px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132324%2F4.-cartwheel-penny-royalmint.com_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22373%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132324%2F4.-cartwheel-penny-royalmint.com_.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132324%2F4.-cartwheel-penny-royalmint.com_-300x295.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06132324%2F4.-cartwheel-penny-royalmint.com_-1024x1007.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678597%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22367%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBritannia%20on%20the%20cartwheel%20penny%2C%201797.%20(Screenshot%20from%20the%20Royal%20Mint%E2%80%99s%20website)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBetween%20the%201730s%20and%20the%201790s%2C%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20transformed%20from%20a%20trading%20body%20to%20an%20imperial%20power.%20These%20changes%20can%20be%20traced%20by%20looking%20at%20the%20two%20Britannia%20sculptures.%20The%20marble%20relief%20completed%20in%201730%2C%20sequestered%20within%20the%20most%20private%20room%20of%20East%20India%20House%2C%20symbolised%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20commercial%20wealth%2C%20which%20relied%20on%20trade%20with%20India%2C%20Africa%2C%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20In%20the%20following%20decades%2C%20the%20Company%20emerged%20as%20an%20imperial%20power%20by%20establishing%20an%20army%20and%20waging%20brutal%20wars%20in%20India.%20By%20the%20late%201790s%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20was%20a%20political%20entity%20that%20sought%20a%20benevolent%20public%20image.%20The%20sculpture%20of%20Britannia%20above%20the%20entrance%20to%20East%20India%20House%20was%20recognisable%20to%20anyone%20with%20a%20penny%20in%20their%20pocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJennifer%20Howes%20is%20an%20art%20historian%20and%20archeologist%2C%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Art%20of%20a%20Corporation%3A%20The%20East%20India%20Company%20as%20Patron%20and%20Collector%3Cem%3E.%20She%20tweets%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjhowesuk%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3E%40jhowesuk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696584601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06131950%2F1.-Foster-8.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fas-the-east-india-company-expanded-its-relationship-with-britannia-kept-changing%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20paintings%20and%20sculptures%20inside%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20headquarters%20were%20almost%20solely%20of%20men%20who%20served%20it%2C%20women%20were%20only%20symbols.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fas-the-east-india-company-expanded-its-relationship-with-britannia-kept-changing%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iranian%20Women's%20Rights%20Activist%20Narges%20Mohammadi%20is%202023%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20Winner%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06143815%2FF7vqXLaXwAAm3lu.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Iranian%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20activist%20Narges%20Mohammadi%20was%20on%20Friday%20(October%206)%20awarded%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20for%202023%20for%20her%20fight%20against%20the%20oppression%20of%20women%20in%20Iran%20and%20her%20fight%20to%20promote%20human%20rights%20and%20freedom%20for%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHer%20brave%20struggle%20has%20come%20with%20tremendous%20personal%20costs.%20Altogether%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20arrested%20her%2013%20times%2C%20convicted%20her%20five%20times%2C%20and%20sentenced%20her%20to%20a%20total%20of%2031%20years%20in%20prison%20and%20154%20lashes.%20Ms%20Mohammadi%20is%20still%20in%20prison%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Nobel%20Institute%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20referred%20to%20the%20protests%20in%20September%202022%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Mahsa%20Amini%20in%20the%20custody%20of%20the%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20morality%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMohammadi%20is%20the%20second%20Iranian%20woman%20to%20received%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize.%20Before%20her%2C%20Shirin%20Ebadi%20was%20awarded%20the%20prize%20in%202003.%20The%20two%20women%E2%80%99s%20paths%20crossed%20when%20Mohammadi%20began%20involved%20with%20the%20Defenders%20of%20Human%20Rights%20Center%2C%20founded%20by%20Ebadi%20in%20Tehran.%20In%202011%2C%20Mohammadi%20was%20arrested%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20sentenced%20to%20many%20years%20of%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20release%20on%20bail%2C%20Mohammadi%20began%20a%20campaign%20against%20the%20use%20of%20the%20death%20penalty%20in%20Iran%2C%20which%20executes%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20inhabitants%20annually.%20She%20was%20arrested%20again%20in%202015.%20In%20prison%2C%20she%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20regime%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%20use%20of%20torture%20and%20sexualised%20violence%20against%20political%20prisoners%2C%20especially%20women%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20article%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20one-year%20anniversary%20of%20Mahsa%20Amini%E2%80%99s%20killing%2C%20which%20Mohammadi%20smuggled%20out%20of%20prison%2C%20she%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20more%20of%20us%20they%20lock%20up%2C%20the%20stronger%20we%20become.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENarges%20Mohammadi%20is%20a%20woman%2C%20a%20human%20rights%20advocate%2C%20and%20a%20freedom%20fighter.%20In%20awarding%20her%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%2C%20the%20Norwegian%20Nobel%20Committee%20wishes%20to%20honour%20her%20courageous%20fight%20for%20human%20rights%2C%20freedom%2C%20and%20democracy%20in%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nobel%20Institute%20said%20that%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Peace%20Prize%20also%20%E2%80%9Crecognises%20the%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20who%2C%20in%20the%20preceding%20year%2C%20have%20demonstrated%20against%20the%20theocratic%20regime%E2%80%99s%20policies%20of%20discrimination%20and%20oppression%20targeting%20women%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696584366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06143815%2FF7vqXLaXwAAm3lu.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Firan-womens-rights-activist-narges-mohammadi-2023-nobel-peace-prize%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHer%20brave%20struggle%20has%20come%20with%20tremendous%20personal%20costs.%20Altogether%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20arrested%20her%2013%20times%2C%20convicted%20he