%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fextreme-floods-and-fires-is-climate-change-to-blame%2Fa-66881959%5C%22%3Eclimate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20to%20over%2043%20million%20displacements%20involving%20children%20between%202016%20and%202021%2C%20according%20to%20a%20United%20Nations%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20current%20rate%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20more%20than%20100%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-young-people-sue-32-european-nations%2Fa-66937734%5C%22%3Echildren%20and%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0could%C2%A0be%20displaced%20by%20weather%20disasters%20alone%20over%20the%20next%2030%20years%2C%20the%20report%20released%20by%20UNICEF%20on%20Friday%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reality%20is%20that%20far%20more%20children%20are%20going%20to%20be%20impacted%20in%20(the)%20future%2C%20as%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20continue%20to%20intensify%2C%E2%80%9D%20Laura%20Healy%2C%20a%20migration%20specialist%20at%20UNICEF%20and%20one%20of%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENumbers%20on%20internal%20displacements%20caused%20by%20climate%20disasters%20do%20not%20generally%20account%20for%20the%20age%20of%20the%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20UN%20children%E2%80%99s%20agency%20worked%20with%20the%20non-governmental%20Internal%20Displacement%20Monitoring%20Center%20to%20sift%20through%20the%20data%20and%20highlight%20the%20hidden%20tally%20on%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajority%20displaced%20due%20to%20floods%20and%20storms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%202016%20to%202021%2C%20four%20types%20of%20climate%20disasters%3A%20floods%2C%20storms%2C%20droughts%20and%20wildfires%20led%20to%20the%20displacement%20of%2043.1%20million%20children%20in%2044%20countries%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20frequency%20of%20these%20disasters%20has%20increased%20due%20to%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20displacements%2C%2095%20per%20cent%20(40.9%20million)%20were%20caused%20by%20floods%20and%20storms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20over%201.3%20million%20children%20were%20displaced%20within%20their%20countries%20because%20of%20droughts%2C%20nearly%20810%2C000%20children%20were%20displaced%20because%20of%20forest%20fires%2C%20mainly%20in%20Canada%2C%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20report%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20the%20Philippines%20were%20among%20the%20nations%20where%20the%20most%20children%20were%20internally%20displaced%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20relative%20to%20the%20size%20of%20the%20child%20population%2C%20children%20living%20in%20small%20island%20countries%2C%20like%20Dominica%20and%20Vanuatu%2C%20were%20most%20affected%20by%20storms%2C%20while%20children%20in%20Somalia%20and%20South%20Sudan%20were%20most%20affected%20by%20floods%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20terrifying%20for%20any%20child%20when%20a%20ferocious%20wildfire%2C%20storm%20or%20flood%20barrels%20into%20their%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20UNICEF%20Executive%20Director%20Catherine%20Russell%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20those%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20flee%2C%20the%20fear%20and%20impact%20can%20be%20especially%20devastating%2C%20with%20worry%20of%20whether%20they%20will%20return%20home%2C%20resume%20school%2C%20or%20be%20forced%20to%20move%20again.%20Moving%20may%20have%20saved%20their%20lives%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20very%20disruptive%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussell%20raised%20concern%20about%20acting%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20slowly%E2%80%9D%20in%20tackling%20the%20spiralling%20challenge%20for%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20escalate%2C%20so%20too%20will%20climate-driven%20movement.%20We%20have%20the%20tools%20and%20knowledge%20to%20respond%20to%20this%20escalating%20challenge%20for%20children%2C%20but%20we%20are%20acting%20far%20too%20slowly.%20We%20need%20to%20strengthen%20efforts%20to%20prepare%20communities%2C%20protect%20children%20at%20risk%20of%20displacement%2C%20and%20support%20those%20already%20uprooted%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funicef-millions-of-children-displaced-due-to-extreme-weather-events%2Fa-67013735%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696583148000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F24190056%2F8529842277_c1994cb396_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Funicef-extreme-weather-displaced-millions-children%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20UN%20report%20says%20that%20more%20than%2043%20million%20children%20were%20uprooted%20between%202016%20and%202021%20due%20to%20weather%20disasters%20fuelled%20by%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Funicef-extreme-weather-displaced-millions-children%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20the%20Year%20Of%20The%20Lowest%20MGNREGS%20Allocation%2C%2093%25%20Budget%20Used%20in%20Just%20Six%20Months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17104216%2F8972253839_fb25825498_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nearly%2093%25%20of%20the%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore%20budget%20allocated%20to%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Scheme%20(MGNREGS)%20for%20this%20financial%20year%20has%20been%20used%20in%20just%20the%20first%20half%20of%20year%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%20Economic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Fwork-demand-under-rural-jobs-scheme-rises-in-h1%2Farticleshow%2F104195784.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20demand%20for%20work%20under%20the%20rural%20employment%20scheme%20also%20increased%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20depth%20of%20an%20industrial%20recovery%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20rural%20development%20ministry%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Fwork-demand-under-rural-jobs-scheme-rises-in-h1%2Farticleshow%2F104195784.cms%5C%22%3Eseek%20%E2%80%9Csubstantial%E2%80%9D%20supplementary%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0funds%20to%20run%20the%20scheme%20throughout%20this%20fiscal%20year.%20The%20fund%20requirement%20is%20high%20despite%20the%20suspension%20of%20MGNREGS%20work%20in%20West%20Bengal%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20main%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20statement%20released%20on%20Thursday%20(October%205)%2C%20the%20Union%20rural%20development%20ministry%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFunds%20of%20State%20of%20West%20Bengal%20have%20been%20stopped%20from%20March%209%2C%202022%20as%20per%20provision%20of%20Section%2027%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%2C%202005%20due%20to%20non-compliance%20of%20directives%20of%20Central%20Government%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20there%20were%20no%20fund%20constraints%20for%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPreliminary%20data%20compiled%20by%20the%20rural%20development%20ministry%20also%20suggests%20that%20person-days%20under%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20the%20total%20number%20of%20work%20days%20by%20a%20person%20registered%20under%20the%20scheme%20in%20a%20financial%20year%20%E2%80%93%20has%20already%20hit%2082%25%20of%20the%20full-year%20target%20so%20far.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerson-days%20generated%20under%20the%20scheme%20rose%20close%20to%209%25%20between%20April%20and%20September%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%20to%20almost%20187%20crore%2C%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20number%20of%20individuals%20who%20opted%20for%20work%20under%20the%20scheme%20until%20September%20also%20increased%20by%204.6%25%20to%20about%2019%20crore%20in%202023%20compared%20to%20the%20year%20before.%20Additionally%2C%20members%20of%2015%20crore%20households%20demanded%20work%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20up%208.5%25%20from%20a%20year%20before%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Fwork-demand-under-rural-jobs-scheme-rises-in-h1%2Farticleshow%2F104195784.cms%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20budgetary%20allocation%20to%20MGNREGS%20has%20come%20under%20the%20scanner%20as%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20allocation%20was%2032%25%20less%20than%20the%20current%20financial%20year%E2%80%99s%20revised%20estimate%20of%20Rs%2089%2C400%20crore%20and%20just%20a%20little%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20budget%20estimate%20of%20Rs%201%2C11%2C500%20crores%20of%202020-21%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fspecials%2Fmgnregs-budget-cut-squeezing-a-lifeline-for-rural-poor-1189999.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFinance%2520Minister%2520Nirmala%2520Sitharaman%2520has%2C11%252C500%2520crores%2520of%25202020%252D21.%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20allocation%2C%20under%200.2%25%20of%20the%20GDP%2C%20is%20the%20lowest%20MGNREGS%20allocation%20ever.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696582776000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17104216%2F8972253839_fb25825498_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fin-the-year-of-the-lowest-mgnregs-allocation-93-budget-used-in-just-six-months%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rural%20development%20ministry%20will%20seek%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%26quot%3B%20supplementary%20funds%20to%20run%20the%20scheme%20throughout%20this%20fiscal%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fin-the-year-of-the-lowest-mgnregs-allocation-93-budget-used-in-just-six-months%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20Can%E2%80%99t%20Stop%20Government%20From%20Acting%20on%20Data%2C%20Says%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2F05025948%2FIMG_3500.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20(October%206)%20refused%20to%20pass%20any%20order%20restraining%20the%20Bihar%20government%20from%20acting%20on%20the%20data%20it%20has%20collected%20through%20the%20caste%20survey.%20Hearing%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20court%20adjourned%20the%20hearing%20until%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20stop%20state%20government%20or%20any%20government%20from%20taking%20a%20decision%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20S.V.N.%20Bhatti%20remarked%20orally%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bihar-caste-survey-refuses-to-restrain-bihar-govt-from-acting-on-caste-survey-data-239479%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20petitions%20were%20filed%20by%20Youth%20for%20Equality%20and%20Ek%20Soch%20Ek%20Prayas%2C%20two%20NGOs%2C%20challenging%20the%20Patna%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20in%20August%20upholding%20the%20Bihar%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20conduct%20a%20caste%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20advocate%20Aparajitha%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20appearing%20for%20the%20petitioners%20%E2%80%93%20took%20exception%20to%20the%20state%20government%20releasing%20the%20caste%20composition%20data%20earlier%20this%20week%20while%20the%20matter%20was%20sub-judice.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20preempted%20the%20court.%20We%20were%20arguing%20stay%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20collect%20caste%20details%20violated%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20recognised%20privacy%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20The%20state%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20show%20any%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20purpose%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20lawyer%20argued%2C%20seeking%20an%20interim%20status%20quo%20order%20asking%20the%20government%20not%20to%20act%20upon%20the%20survey%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Justice%20Khanna%20asked%20the%20state%20why%20the%20data%20was%20published%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Shyam%20Divan%20indicated%20that%20there%20was%20no%20order%20preventing%20such%20a%20move.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20court%20indicated%20that%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20it%20will%20decide%20whether%20notice%20is%20to%20be%20issued%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20observed%20that%20the%20matter%20requires%20to%20be%20heard%20at%20length%20and%20adjourned%20the%20hearing.%20It%20issued%20a%20formal%20notice%20to%20the%20state%20government%20on%20the%20petitions.%20While%20Singh%20reiterated%20the%20plea%20for%20status%20quo%2C%20the%20bench%20categorically%20declined%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20stop%20state%20government%20or%20any%20government%20from%20taking%20a%20decision.%20That%20would%20be%20wrong.%20But%2C%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20issue%20with%20regards%20to%20data%2C%20that%20will%20be%20considered.%20We%20are%20going%20to%20examine%20the%20other%20issue%20regarding%20the%20power%20of%20the%20state%20government%20to%20conduct%20this%20exercise%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbeyond-politics-caste-census-deepening-india-social-justice-paradigm%5C%22%3EBeyond%20Politics%3A%20Caste%20Census%20Is%20About%20Deepening%20India%E2%80%99s%20Social%20Justice%20Paradigm%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-census-released-at-63-obc-ebc-groups-set-to-take-pole-position-in-state-politics%5C%22%3Ereleased%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%C2%A0extremely%20backward%20classes%20(EBC)%20constituted%2036.01%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20while%20other%20backward%20classes%20(OBC)%20contributed%20an%20additional%2027.12%25.%20Collectively%2C%20these%20groups%20make%20up%2063.13%25%20of%20the%2013-crore%20population%20of%20the%20state%2C%20while%20nearly%2020%25%20belong%20to%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20and%201.6%25%20to%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST).%20The%20general%20category%20accounts%20for%20around%2015%25%2C%20the%20data%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20caste%20survey%20was%20launched%20in%20Bihar%20in%20January%20this%20year%2C%20which%20the%20government%20said%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20frame%20policies%20that%20would%20help%20uplift%20disadvantaged%20groups.%20The%20survey%20was%20halted%20temporarily%20in%20May%20by%20the%20Patna%20high%20court.%20In%20August%2C%20the%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpatna-high-court-dismisses-petitions-against-bihar-caste-census%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20exercise%20was%20%E2%80%98perfectly%20valid%E2%80%99%20and%20initiated%20with%20due%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20caste%20census%20has%20become%20a%20political%20issue%2C%20with%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20of%20opposition%20parties%20pressuring%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20conduct%20such%20an%20exercise%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20While%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA%20government%20conducted%20a%20Socio-Economic%20and%20Caste%20Census%20(SECC)%20in%202011-12%2C%20the%20data%20was%20never%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696581302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2F05025948%2FIMG_3500.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbihar-caste-survey-cant-stop-govt-from-acting-on-data-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hearing%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20court%20adjourned%20the%20hearing%20until%20January%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbihar-caste-survey-cant-stop-govt-from-acting-on-data-sc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Beyond%20Politics%3A%20Caste%20Census%20Is%20About%20Deepening%20India%E2%80%99s%20Social%20Justice%20Paradigm%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F07202552%2FScreenshot-2022-02-07-at-8.25.47-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EB.R.%20Ambedkar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLfVyDwAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPT412%26lpg%3DPT412%26dq%3Da%2Bnation%2Bis%2Bnot%2Ba%2Bpeople%2Bsynthesised%2Bby%2Ba%2Bcommon%2Bculture%2Bderived%2Bfrom%2Bcommon%2Blanguage%2C%2Bcommon%2Breligion%2Bor%2Bcommon%2Brace...Nationality%2Bis%2Ba%2Bfeeling%2Bof%2Boneness%2Bwhich%2Bmakes%2Bthose%2Bwho%2Bare%2Bcharged%2Bwith%2Bit%2Bfeel%2Bthey%2Bare%2Bkith%2Band%2Bkin...It%2Bis%2Ba%2Bfeeling%2Bof%2B%25E2%2580%259Cconsciousness%2Bof%2Bkind%25E2%2580%259D...it%2Bis%2Blonging%2Bto%2Bbelonging%2Bto%2Bone%25E2%2580%2599s%2Bown%2Bgroup.%2BThis%2Bis%2Bthe%2Bessence%2Bof%2Bwhat%2Bis%2Bcalled%2Ba%2Bnationality%2Band%2Bnational%2Bfeeling%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3DWGzhKld30d%26sig%3DACfU3U0Fa_8nssnpfTPkMDVT6xg2G9laHQ%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D2ahUKEwjJp7H8nPbzAhXj8XMBHSkiCl8Q6AF6BAgQEAM%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Da%2520nation%2520is%2520not%2520a%2520people%2520synthesised%2520by%2520a%2520common%2520culture%2520derived%2520from%2520common%2520language%2C%2520common%2520religion%2520or%2520common%2520race...Nationality%2520is%2520a%2520feeling%2520of%2520oneness%2520which%2520makes%2520those%2520who%2520are%2520charged%2520with%2520it%2520feel%2520they%2520are%2520kith%2520and%2520kin...It%2520is%2520a%2520feeling%2520of%2520%25E2%2580%259Cconsciousness%2520of%2520kind%25E2%2580%259D...it%2520is%2520longing%2520to%2520belonging%2520to%2520one%25E2%2580%2599s%2520own%2520group.%2520This%2520is%2520the%2520essence%2520of%2520what%2520is%2520called%2520a%2520nationality%2520and%2520national%2520feeling%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3Efamously%20posited%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20nation%20is%20not%20a%20people%20synthesised%20by%20a%20common%20culture%20derived%20from%20a%20common%20language%2C%20a%20common%20religion%20or%20a%20common%20race.%20Nationality%20is%20a%20feeling%20of%20oneness%20which%20makes%20those%20who%20are%20charged%20with%20it%20feel%20they%20are%20kith%20and%20kin.%20It%20is%20a%20feeling%20of%20%E2%80%98consciousness%20of%20kind%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20a%20longing%20to%20belong%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20group.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20exhortation%2C%20and%20the%20efforts%20of%20numerous%20governments%20after%201947%2C%20caste%20discrimination%20continues%20to%20be%20prevalent%20in%20India.%20Millions%20of%20Indians%20are%20systematically%20denied%20access%20to%20the%20great%20vaults%20of%20this%20nation%20and%20continue%20to%20be%20unequal%20partners%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20unspoken%20consensus%20among%20the%20select%20sections%20of%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20the%20media%2C%20the%20corporate%20sector%2C%20and%20even%20political%20parties%2C%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKamandal%3C%2Fem%3E%20politics%20was%20a%20necessary%20evil%20to%20reverse%20%3Cem%3EMandal%3C%2Fem%3E%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDesigned%20to%20perpetuate%20caste%20hegemonies%2C%20this%20unstated%20consensus%20has%20deliberately%20stymied%20numerous%20progressive%20policy%20and%20programmatic%20measures%20meant%20to%20empower%20the%20people%20belonging%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20(SC)%2C%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20(ST)%2C%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBC)%2C%20and%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20why%20there%20was%20concerted%20resistance%20to%20the%20release%20of%20the%20Socio-Economic%20Caste%20Census%20(SECC)%20data%2C%20or%20to%20conduct%20a%20fresh%20caste%20census%20(as%20the%20BJP%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-govt-defensive-over-bihar-caste-survey-changes-affidavit-in-supreme-court%5C%22%3Ehas%20stated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20both%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20in%20parliament).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20caste%20survey%20and%20the%20Indian%20National%20Developmental%20Inclusive%20Alliance%E2%80%99s%20(INDIA)%20strident%20championing%20of%20the%20caste%20census%20offer%20a%20rare%20window%20of%20opportunity%20to%20meaningfully%20debate%20how%20India%E2%80%99s%20social%20justice%20paradigm%20can%20be%20deepened.%20Both%20moral%20and%20political%20considerations%20mandate%20that%20India%20leverage%20this%20debate%20to%20take%20a%20principled%20stand%20on%20some%20critical%20social%20justice%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-census-bjp-india-bloc%5C%22%3EBihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20Why%20the%20BJP%20Is%20Jittery%20and%20INDIA%20Bloc%20Upbeat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EINDIA%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20social%20justice%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMorally%2C%20there%20are%20two%20reasons%20why%20the%20INDIA%20parties%20are%20taking%20a%20principled%20stand%20on%20social%20justice%20issues.%20Firstly%2C%20despite%20decades%20of%20reservations%20in%20government%20services%2C%20only%2011.5%25%20of%20the%20A-class%20administrative%20positions%20in%20India%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gservants.com%2F2012%2F12%2F28%2Femployment-of-other-backaward-classes-obcs-and-scsts-in-central-government-jobs-groups-a-to-d%2F%5C%22%3Eoccupied%20by%20SCs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2013.5%25%20by%20OBCs.%20Similarly%2C%2095%25%20of%20employed%20SCs%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthirdworld.nl%2Fthe-allocation-of-publicly-provided-goods-to-rural-households-in-india-on-some-consequences-of-caste-religion-and-democracy%5C%22%3Eclustered%20in%20grades%20C%20and%20D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%2022.6%25%20of%20OBCs%20are%20employed%20in%20Group%20C.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Ftodays-paper%2Ftp-national%2Fupper-castes-dominate-national-media-says-survey-in-delhi%2Farticle3115113.ece%5C%22%3Esurvey%20on%20the%20social%20profiles%20of%20senior%20decision-makers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%2037%20newspapers%20and%20television%20channels%20found%20that%2090%25%20of%20the%20decision-makers%20in%20the%20English%20language%20print%20media%20and%2079%25%20in%20television%20channels%20belonged%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20community.%20Likewise%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwid.world%2Fdocument%2Fn-k-bharti-wealth-inequality-class-and-caste-in-india-1961-2012%2F%5C%22%3Eaverage%20household%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20is%20Rs%201%2C13%2C%20222%20(approximately%20Rs%209%2C435%20per%20month)%2C%20ST%2C%20SCs%20and%20OBCs%20earned%2034%25%2C%2021%25%20and%208%25%2C%20respectively.%20This%20is%20less%20than%20the%20national%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Ambedkar%20presciently%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9Cby%20reason%20of%20our%20social%20and%20economic%20structure%2C%20(we)%20continue%20to%20deny%20the%20principle%20of%20one%20man%20one%20value%E2%80%9D%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20SCs%2C%20STs%2C%20OBCs%2C%20and%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20structural%20discrimination%20is%20being%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20BJP%20government%2C%20which%20takes%20inspiration%20from%20M.S.%20Golwalkar%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fin.ernet.dli.2015.489044%2Fpage%2F3%2Fmode%2F2up%5C%22%3Eargument%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20reservations%20are%20%E2%80%9Cdivisive%20talk%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20must%20cry%20a%20complete%20halt%20to%20forming%20groups%20based%20on%20caste%E2%80%A6and%20demanding%20rights%20and%20privileges%20in%20services%2C%20financial%20aids%2C%20admission%20in%20educational%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FBunch-of-Thoughts%2Fdp%2F8186595198%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBunch%20of%20Thoughts%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20p.%20351).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3Eslashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20SCSP-TSP%20fund%20(renamed%20as%20the%20Special%20Central%20Assistance%20to%20SCs%20and%20STs)%20by%2050%25%2C%20looked%20the%20other%20way%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2Fgau-raksha-and-war-against-indias-poor%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Egau%20rakshaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20target%20Dalits%20for%20their%20vocations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20undermined%20affirmative%20action%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fupsc-civil-services-examination-13-point-200-point-quota-roster-conundrum-5621525%2F%5C%22%3Echanging%20the%20unit%20of%20reservation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2020%2Fsep%2F21%2Fno-funds-released-for-rehabilitation-of-manual-scavengers-earlier-funds-unutilized-govt-2199858.html%5C%22%3Eslashed%20and%20under-utilised%20the%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20rehabilitation%20of%20manual%20scavengers%2C%20while%20its%20ideological%20collaborators%20have%20repeatedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Frss-chief-mohan-bhagwat-calls-for-dialogue-on-reservation%2Farticle29129128.ece%5C%22%3Easked%20for%20a%20review%20of%20reservations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20All%20this%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fgovernance%2Fcrimes-against-sc-st-women-children-up-15-but-conviction-rate-low-says-house-panel%2F626548%2F%5C%22%3Eatrocities%20against%20SCs%2FSTs%20have%20increased%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20light%2C%20conducting%20the%20caste%20census%20would%20provide%20a%20scientific%20basis%20to%20map%20socio-economic%20and%20educational%20backwardness%20for%20all%20communities%2C%20and%20not%20just%20the%20SCs%2C%20STs%2C%20OBCs%2C%20but%20also%20the%20economically%20weaker%20sections%20among%20the%20dominant%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes.%20This%20would%20ensure%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20welfare%20programmes%20are%20customised.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESurely%20the%20targeted%20delivery%20of%20benefits%20and%20services%20to%20those%20really%20in%20need%20as%20well%20as%20the%20consequent%20curtailment%20of%20leakages%2Frent-seeking%20etc.%20are%20desirable%20goals%20for%20any%20government%20committed%20to%20furthering%20the%20public%20good.%20No%20one%20working%20in%20the%20national%20interest%20could%20possibly%20oppose%20this%2C%20although%20there%20are%20those%20who%20have%20myopically%20argued%20that%20conducting%20the%20caste%20census%20could%20unleash%20fissiparous%20tendencies%20and%20hence%20tear%20India%E2%80%99s%20social%20fabric.%20Sadly%2C%20such%20arguments%20reek%20of%20unchecked%20privilege.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20152646%2FF1PwVKDXoAUTyA3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20152646%2FF1PwVKDXoAUTyA3.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20152646%2FF1PwVKDXoAUTyA3-300x134.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20152646%2FF1PwVKDXoAUTyA3-1024x457.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664149%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22536%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJoint%20opposition%20parties%20meeting%20in%20Bengaluru.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40INCIndia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20need%20for%20championing%20the%20caste%20census%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20the%20INDIA%20parties%20must%20champion%20an%20inspiring%20vision%20premised%20on%20social%20justice%20because%20the%20BJP%20has%20methodically%20spearheaded%20the%20ethnicisation%20of%20Indian%20politics%20for%20its%20own%20politico-ideological%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20symbolically%20accommodated%20the%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20OBC%20community%20leaders%20in%20its%20party%20organisation%20and%20various%20cabinets.%20Arguably%2C%20this%20unfavourable%20inclusion%20is%20instrumental%2C%20for%20none%20of%20these%20leaders%20enjoys%20any%20real%20power%20or%20influence.%20However%2C%20it%20does%20offer%20upward%20social%20and%20political%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20leveraged%20these%20leaders%20to%20methodically%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20OBC%20and%20Dalit%20sub-castes%2C%20co-opt%20their%20icons%20and%20re-engineer%20their%20thinking%20towards%20a%20larger%20ideological%20agenda%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EThis%20has%20paid%20rich%20dividends%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fbjp-vote-share-caste-census-7466088%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20the%20National%20Election%20Studies%20show%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBucking%20earlier%20trends%2C%2044%25%20of%20the%20OBCs%20voted%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%202019%2C%20while%20only%2027%25%20voted%20for%20regional%20parties.%20Dissecting%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fbjp-vote-share-caste-census-7466088%2F%5C%22%3Eeven%20further%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20what%20emerges%20is%20that%2041%25%20of%20the%20OBC%20dominant%20sub-castes%20voted%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20while%2047%25%20of%20the%20OBC%20sub-castes%20voted%20for%20it%20in%20the%20same%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20and%20most%20problematically%2C%20this%20is%20part%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20larger%20strategy%20to%20foster%20a%20macro-identity%20around%20Hindi%2C%20Hindu%20and%20Hindustan%2C%20and%20then%20cynically%20deploy%20this%20bloc%20against%20those%20that%20Golwalkar%20perceived%20to%20be%20the%20real%20enemies%2C%20namely%20Christians%20and%20Muslims%20(as%20well%20as%20ideological%20dissidents).%20Progressive%20parties%20cannot%20counter%20this%20by%20skirting%20around%20the%20caste%20census%20issue%20(or%20the%20allied%20issues%20that%20emanate%20from%20it).%20That%20would%20essentially%20mean%20giving%20a%20blank%20cheque%20to%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20way%20to%20disrupt%20the%20status%20quo%20is%20through%20normative%20and%20disruptive%20reforms%2C%20something%20the%20INDIA%20parties%20are%20doing%20by%20championing%20the%20caste%20census.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20other%20allied%20policy%20issues%20flowing%20from%20the%20caste%20census%20debate%20that%20could%20very%20substantially%20deepen%20India%E2%80%99s%20social%20justice%20paradigm.%20These%20include%20making%20the%20media%20and%20the%20judiciary%20more%20representative%2C%20filling%20up%20the%20backlog%20in%20reserved%20seats%2C%20reserving%20seats%20for%20OBCs%20in%20legislatures%2C%20taking%20affirmative%20action%20in%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20lie%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20this%20article%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20the%20political%20churning%20that%20is%20about%20to%20begin%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20perhaps%20inevitable%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20aligned%20organisations%20will%20leverage%20these%20to%20caricature%20the%20caste%20census%20as%20antithetical%20to%20the%20interests%20of%20dominant%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes.%20It%20would%2C%20therefore%2C%20be%20expedient%20for%20the%20INDIA%20parties%20to%20anticipate%20this%20%3Cem%3Emanufactured%3C%2Fem%3E%20counter-revolution%2C%20and%20take%20measures%20to%20circumvent%20these%20by%20posing%20an%20inspiring%20economic%20and%20political%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20ways%20they%20can%20begin%20to%20do%20this%20immediately%20is%20by%20extending%20reservations%20for%20the%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20OBC%20communities%20in%20their%20respective%20party%20organisations%2C%20as%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20has%20done.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fres.cloudinary.com%2Fdkplc2mbj%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fv1695636030%2FText_Congress_Consitution_English_15_July_2023_Final_4b6c600ed6.pdf%5C%22%3ERead%3C%2Fa%3E%20Article%20XI-A%5Ba%5D%20of%20the%20Congress%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20reserves%2050%25%20of%20all%20posts%20in%20the%20party%20organisation%20for%20SC-ST-OBC-Minorities).%20That%20can%20be%20followed%20by%20other%20progressive%20measures%20that%20can%20be%20implemented%20through%20the%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20any%20patriotic%20Indian%20interested%20in%20national%20integration%20will%20wholeheartedly%20support%20this%20rare%20opportunity%20to%20unleash%20India%E2%80%99s%20third%20democratic%20upsurge.%20This%20is%20because%20it%20will%20ensure%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20promise%20is%20accorded%20to%20all%20Indians%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20caste%2C%20creed%20or%20ideological%20inclination.%20This%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20ensuring%20that%20no%20one%20gets%20left%2C%20or%20held%20behind.%20To%20paraphrase%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20in%20the%20national%20interest%2C%20let%20us%20therefore%20collectively%20strive%20to%20rebuild%20the%20noble%20mansion%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPushparaj%20Deshpande%20is%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Samruddha%20Bharat%20Foundation%20and%20editor%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ERethinking%20India%3Cem%3E%20series%20(Penguin).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696579523000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F07202552%2FScreenshot-2022-02-07-at-8.25.47-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbeyond-politics-caste-census-deepening-india-social-justice-paradigm%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20an%20unstated%20consensus%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Kamandal%20politics%20is%20a%20necessary%20evil%20to%20reverse%20Mandal%20politics.%20It%20perpetuated%20caste%20hegemonies%20and%20stymied%20numerous%20progressive%20policy%20measures.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%E2%80%99s%20championing%20of%20the%20caste%20census%20offers%20a%20rare%20window%20to%20unleash%20India%E2%80%99s%20third%20democratic%20upsurge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbeyond-politics-caste-census-deepening-india-social-justice-paradigm%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20awarded%20to%20jailed%20Iranian%20activist%20for%20'fight%20against%20oppression%20of%20women'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696574940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F70x70%2Fskynews-narges-mohammadi-nobel-peace-prize_6310771.jpg%3F20231006100648%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnobel-peace-prize-awarded-to-irans-narges-mohammadi-12978009%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jailed%20Iranian%20women's%20rights%20activist%20Narges%20Mohammadi%20has%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20for%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A608%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnobel-peace-prize-awarded-to-irans-narges-mohammadi-12978009%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnobel-peace-prize-awarded-to-irans-narges-mohammadi-12978009%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnobel-peace-prize-awarded-to-irans-narges-mohammadi-12978009%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%2040%20people%20dead%20after%20glacial%20lake%20flooding%20in%20Indian%20Himalayas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696567380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-india-flooding_6309555.jpg%3F20231005081729%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fat-least-40-people-dead-after-glacial-lake-flooding-in-indias-himalayan-region-12977956%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%2040%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20flooding%20in%20the%20Indian%20Himalayan%20region%2C%20officials%20have%2